title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Beat until firm.
Add oleo, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Also makes good caramel cake icing.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
After draining spaghetti, add margarine.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered pie plate (I use casserole dish).
Cook ground beef, onion and pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender; drain.
Add undrained tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; heat and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of "crust."
Fill with meat and tomato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: bite size cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, carrot and honey. Chill 1 hour. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll in chopped pecans. Cover and chill up to 24 hours. Just before serving, insert pretzel stick into each ball.

title: homemade fudge(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and vanilla, in a large pot; bring to a boil. Continue boiling for about 4 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla and pecans. Beat until this mixture starts to thicken. Pour into a pan to cool. Cut into servings. (Cook 2 minutes and this makes great frosting for cake.)

title: caramel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Empty condensed milk into a casserole dish. Place dish on a baking pan. Fill baking pan halfway with water (this is important because it will keep the milk from scalding). Cover the casserole dish with aluminum foil. Bake 2 hours or until milk is caramel colored. Break up any large lumps in the filling before pouring into the crust. Let cool for an hour before spreading Cool Whip on top. The pie must be refrigerated overnight to set properly. Before serving, garnish with pecans, chocolate and toffee bits.

title: scalloped ham (with cabbage)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Steam or cook cabbage in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and green pepper to white sauce.
Add diced ham.
Place a layer of partially cooked cabbage in greased baking dish, then a layer of ham and cheese sauce mixture.
Repeat layers.
Melt butter or margarine; mix with crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cheese cake(yields 9 to 12 servings)
directions: Mix like pie crust and line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and pretzels.
Press into baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and other 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over crumbs.
Mix cornstarch and pineapple juice; cook until thick.
Cool slightly, then add pineapple.
Spread over layer; refrigerate.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix cream and cheese well and sprinkle ginger on top.
Serve with fresh strawberries.

title: mexican crock-pot
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes or until cheese is well melted.
Serve on Doritos.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix until crumbs. Grease a 15x10 jelly roll pan. Gently pack crumbs into shell to make crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Watch to make sure it does not burn.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 11-inch glass pan.
(Can top with 8 ounce shredded Swiss cheese last 5 minutes of baking time.)
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until light brown.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix like any fruit cake.
Put in tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
The cake is delicious because I followed the recipe.
The Bible is the same way; you never know how good it is for your life until you try the recipe daily.

title: sweet-sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook until onion and pepper are tender; add carrots.
Place in a covered dish or jar and chill overnight.
Serves 10.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in buttermilk. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Heat oven to 400°. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Layer as listed in casserole dish.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth together. Put layer of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken on top of chips.
Pour soups on top of chicken.
Lay slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tropical dogs
directions: Mix honey with peanut butter; spread on hot dog bun.
Peel banana; brush with lemon juice to keep from turning brown.
Place banana
in hot dog bun with peanut butter-honey mixture.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in
bottom
of
large frying pan or Dutch oven. Place potatoes
on	top
of
chicken
along with onion, Parmesan cheese,
oregano,
breadcrumbs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/4 cup water and
oil.
On top place garlic, then drench with paprika. Bake approximately	1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered for the first half
of
the
time,
then
covered.
Place
in serving dish and top with sauteed mushrooms.

title: yogurt and mint drink
directions: Puree all ingredients (except sprigs of mint) in blender. Pour in 4 glasses and garnish with mint sprigs.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder together.
Add milk and mix. Pour over melted oleo or butter.
Combine fruit with sugar if needed, distribute over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or more.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like meal.
Add milk.
Make a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased pan at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: twelve layer salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer the ingredients in the order given, using a large glass bowl.
Prepare one day ahead.
Be sure the Miracle Whip completely covers top of salad.
Especially good for large crowds.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake potatoes until soft.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Take out centers, while hot, saving the skins.
Put potato centers in mixing bowl.
Add next four ingredients and mix at medium speed of electric mixer for three minutes, or mash by hand until smooth and fluffy.
Put mixture in potato skins and sprinkle paprika lightly on the potatoes.
Brown in oven for four minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter; add dates and sugar.
Cook until sugar dissolves (about 5 minutes).
Add Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well; roll into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken wings
directions: Put chicken wings in pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken wings.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetarian roast
directions: Mix and bake in oiled pan 1 hour at 350°.
(This is good!)

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas in bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Add sour cream, milk and Cool Whip. Mix completely with whip.
Pour over bananas.
May layer more than once.
Refrigerate.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat 1 minute at high speed in blender.
Pour in 10-inch well-greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber cinnamon rings
directions: Pour over rings and let stand and seal.

title: dorothy lewis' rhubarb cobbler
directions: Put rhubarb in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on sugar, jello and cake mix.
Pour on water and dot with butter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Place
ham
into
crock-pot.
Rub
brown
sugar
evenly across ham; use more, if needed.
Pour cola over ham, covering half of the ham.
Sprinkle any
remaining
brown
sugar across the cola and ham, stirring
until
completely dissolved.
Cook on low setting for at least 6 hours
or
until
tender (can be cooked overnight).
Turn once while cooking.
Ham will be dark in color. Remove ham from crock-pot
and cover with remaining syrup as gravy topping.
Slice in thin slices and serve.

title: christmas party pinwheels
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and dressing mix until smooth. Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Spread about 3/4 cup on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly; wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for at least two hours.
Slice into 1/2 inch pieces. Yield: 15-20 servings, or only 5 servings if you love them like my family does!

title: chow mein
directions: Combine chow mein, celery, onion, and mushrooms in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Microwave 6 to 10 minutes on High or until meat is set.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Mix in chow mein vegetables, water chestnuts and ginger. Cover.
Microwave for 6 to 10 minutes on High, or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tortilla salsa roll-ups
directions: Stir with a spoon the cream cheese, salsa (1/3 cup), onions, garlic, salt and chili powder until smooth.
Spread heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up jelly roll style and place seam side down on baking sheet.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Slice each roll into bite size pieces.
Place small bowl of salsa on side, if desired, for dipping.

title: mixed vegetable casserole(serves 10)
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery.
Drain excess fat.
Mix with all other remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop mushroom stems and onion.
In a large skillet, saute onion in oil until transparent.
Add 1 package thawed chopped spinach and toss until blended.
Add cream cheese.
Melt and blend cheese thoroughly.
After everything is blended, remove from heat and chop mushroom stems.
Little by little add the four cups of bread crumbs until it all comes together like stuffing.
With fingers, pick up enough of the stuffing mix to place into mushroom cap.
It's okay if it is over the edge or piled high.
Do not pack like you would stuffing in a bird.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs and bananas and blend thoroughly.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture and milk. Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, until bread springs back when lightly touched in center.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Cool completely.
Add garlic salt, mixing well.
Stir in cheese, Bisquick and water.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on large cookie sheets, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This recipe serves 50 people and makes a great appetizer.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk with a spoon.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and oranges.
Crumble cookies and add to mixture.
Best if made the night before and refrigerated.

title: squash pie(tastes just like pumpkin, low-fat and good)
directions: Mash squash after cooking in food processor.
Blend all other ingredients well with squash and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add eggs, mashed bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients and stir until well moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: lemon crumb pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well; stir in milk, lemon juice, rind and salt. Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold into lemon mixture and pour into crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°. Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix the first three ingredients.
Add evaporated milk and butter.
Start on low heat.
Stir until it boils.
Boil on low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: apricot chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of baking pan with oil. Shake chicken in plastic bag with flour and salt.
Place chicken in a single layer in pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Combine apricot preserves, mustard and yogurt.
Spread mixture on chicken.
Bake 30 more minutes.
Before serving, brown almonds lightly in toaster oven.
Sprinkle almonds over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: In 3-quart pan on medium-low heat in hot oil, cook onions until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato paste, brown sugar, oregano, 1 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Over high heat, bring to a boil; reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Prepare shells according to package.
Prepare spinach as label directs.
Pour into bowl; cool.
Stir in all cheese and Ricotta.
Fill each cooked shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon sauce evenly into 14 x 10-inch pan.
Arrange filled shells in sauce.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower-bacon salad
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients; let stand 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: vegetables casserole
directions: Mix vegetables.
Put mushroom soup and sour cream and cheese. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Take out.
Put French fried onions on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: Place the green beans, bacon and salt in a large pot and add water to just cover the beans.
Bring to boil.
Lower the heat and cook, uncovered, at a slow boil for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and enough water to cover all vegetables.
Continue cooking until the potatoes and beans are very tender, at least 20 minutes longer. Drain any water that remains and serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternate, adding flour, etc. and milk.
Add extracts.
Put in large tube pan, well oiled or lined.
Start in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix the pudding with 3 cups of milk; add the Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put layer of graham crackers.
Add on top half of the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture.
Add last layer of graham crackers and spread icing over top.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Keeps very well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients VERY well with hands.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
Cook on heat 1/2 way between low and medium.
After 30 minutes, turn each loaf over. Cook a total of 1 hour.

title: pickled squash
directions: Slice squash, onions and peppers.
Add salt and garlic.
Cover with ice and let stand 3 hours. Drain off water.
Add spices and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Put into jars and seal.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and put Hershey Kiss on immediately.

title: white sauce or cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and salt, stirring until mixed.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
If sauce is too thick, add more milk.
Good for scalloped and creamed dishes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: healthy carrot cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In large bowl, mix applesauce, eggs and grated carrots.
Add dry ingredients. Mix with electric mixer for 2 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cook noodles; drain.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix meat, noodles, onion, green pepper, mushrooms, pepperoni and spaghetti sauce together.
Put in baking dish and cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts.
Delicious with salad and French bread.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift salt, soda and cinnamon 3 times.
Put pecans and apples in dry mixture. Mix with egg mixture.
Bake in floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cider ice
directions: Bring
all
ingredients
to
a	boil
and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove
cinnamon sticks and freeze in shallow trays.
When
ready to serve, remove from freezer for about 10 minutes and
break into pieces.
Serve in sherbet dishes as an appetizer.	Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and zucchini in butter until limp.
Put in blender and blend.
Add curry powder, broth, evaporated milk and salt and pepper; stir.
Serve hot or cold.

title: three things pie
directions: Dissolve candy bar in double boiler.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 1 hour.

title: praline nuts
directions: Put nuts on Teflon cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Stir often.
Remove from oven.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook all but marshmallows together until thick.
Add the marshmallows.
Cook until melted.
Pour over fruit.
Suggested fruit:
1 can pineapple, 1 can fruit cocktail (drained), 1 small can coconut, 2 apples, 1 can mandarin oranges, 4 bananas and strawberries, if desired.

title: to make self-rising flour
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered can or jar and use soon.
Use in any recipe calling for self-rising flour.
Spoon flour lightly into a cup until high.
Do not use the cup as a scoop or shake or tap full cup.
Stir flour lightly with a fork.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients. Add apples, walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle 10x sugar over cooled cake.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cut bread loaf in half.
Roll each half into a square. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
In frying pan, crumble up sausage and add chopped pepper and onion until done.
Drain and mix with 3/4's of the beaten eggs.
Put 1/2 of sausage mixture in middle of each square of bread.
Put grated cheese on top and fold bread up on ends.
Brush with egg mixture and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix together beans, green pepper, onion and celery.
Add to dressing of vinegar, salad oil, pepper, salt and sugar.
(Dressing may be heated until sugar melts.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Add water to canned milk to equal 1 1/2 cups.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in cake.
Slowly pour the mixture over cake.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle with coconut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Dot with butter and bake in casserole dish 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Before serving, top with grated cheese.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Spray your crock-pot lightly. Mix soups together. Place a little soup in bottom of the crock-pot. Cut your steak into serving pieces and place on top of the soup. Place the remainder of soup on top of the steak. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Slice all fruits and mix with orange juice in large bowl.
Put in freezer.
Take out about 2 hours before serving.
Put in individual cups and pour ginger ale over them.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to boil and stir constantly. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, apricot nectar, cream cheese (beat cream cheese until fluffy), nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick and easy pasta soup
directions: Combine tomato sauce and chicken broth.
Prepare pasta according to package.
Microwave mixed vegetables according to package.

title: cheese and beer dip(1 portion)
directions: Note:
This looks awful
at first, but becomes a very smooth mixture.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook 10 to 12 minutes until sugar dissolves the rhubarb, sugar and pineapple.
Turn off heat; stir in jello.
Store in freezer.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread, combine tomatoes, pepper, onions, pimentos & beans & toss.
Combine mayo & pickle juice and stir well.
Layer 1/2 of each of bread, tomato mix, mayo, mix and repeat in a large bowl until you
have layered all of it. Then wait for the compliments.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix and spread over bottom layer. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together and stir into broccoli,
bacon and raisins.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together with mixer and press in 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let
set
in
refrigerator.
Melt
ounce) package chocolate chips.
Spread on top and let set.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix and heat in microwave on High about 2 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers and chips.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by well-rounded tablespoonfuls into small amount of oil in a frying pan over medium heat.
(Do about 4 or 5 at a time.)
Brown on both sides.
Remove to paper towel-lined serving dish.
Can be kept warm in a 200° oven until all are ready.

title: baked apricots
directions: Drain apricots well.
Put a layer of apricot halves in a greased baking dish. Cover with brown sugar.
Add crushed Ritz crackers and dot thickly with butter. Repeat this until dish is full. Add chopped cherries and chopped pecans to top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually until light and fluffy. Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each one.
Stir in vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients together, add gradually to creamed mixture.
Form a ball, cover and chill for 3 hours.
Roll out, cut into shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta with shrimp and garlic sauce
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat; cook garlic and onion until tender.
Add half of the parsley and the shrimp. Cook for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, wine, salt and pepper.
Cook just until shrimp turn opaque and begin to curl.
Remove from heat and reheat just before pasta is ready.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Heat serving bowl and place pasta and sauce together.
Toss.
Cover with remaining parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel for cinnamon rolls
directions: Bring all ingredients just to a boil.
Do not boil.
Keeps very well in the refrigerator.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Put in pot and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Put chicken in a large baking dish or pan.
Pour half of sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 60 minutes.
Baste every 15 minutes with remaining sauce.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix pie crust and cheese well.
Mix Tabasco sauce with 4 tablespoons milk.
Mix with pie crust and cheese mixture.
Use additional tablespoon milk if needed.
Chill dough.
Roll out between 2 pieces wax paper to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out (can use cookie cutters or a knife) and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store up to 2 days or freeze for longer storage.
Store between paper towels.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Save broth from chicken.
Dip tortilla shells in broth and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer chicken, green pepper, onion, cheese, chili powder and salt.
Keep making layers of these until all ingredients are used.
Combine soups and spread over top.
Then squeeze stewed tomatoes over the soup.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread out 2 packages of crescent rolls on an 11 x 15-inch pan and bake.
Cool.
Mix 2 packages of cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix.
Spread over crust and press chopped vegetables into cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic powder in margarine.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Soak crumbs in cream and water in a medium bowl.
Add beef, pork, onion and seasonings. Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Shape into small balls with hands or two teaspoons dipped in cold water.
Fry in butter, shaking pan continuously to keep balls round.
Serve hot or cold as a "Smorgasbord" dish.

title: duck ala orange
directions: Wash duck and remove some of excess fat.
Pat dry.
Put duck in roasting pan with rack underneath.
Set oven to 500°. Prick duck with fork around breast and legs.
Put in oven for 5 to 10 minutes and hear crackling.
Mix frozen orange juice, grated orange peel and honey to taste.
Remove duck and drain fat; return to oven for more crackling and again drain fat.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Baste duck with orange/honey mixture with pastry brush. Cover and roast at 350° until done.
Repeat orange sauce over duck; duck can also be stuffed.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Into a large mixing bowl, put ingredients.
Let soak for 1 hour, then put through blender.
Add salt, garlic salt and pepper to taste.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water. Pour into meal.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk, then beaten eggs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook bacon until very crisp and break into pieces.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve with Italian dressing.
This is a very simple and elegant salad to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° to 375°.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put cinnamon in bag; shake to cover frozen rolls.
In Bundt pan, buttered well, add sugar, then raisins and rolls.
Let dough rise to top of pan (overnight) covered.
Sprinkle with pudding (dry) then add melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Invert to serving dish as soon as you remove from oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Rinse beef and chop fine.
Blend remaining ingredients with beef.
Roll in ball; spread walnuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer. Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar and butter in large bowl. Stir in eggs until well blended. Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat until smooth. Stir in flour just until moistened. Stir in nuts and pour into pans. Bake about 1 hour. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in double boiler until blended. Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels plus vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Transfer chocolate mix to a large bowl. Beat in eggs, one at a time.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onions and peppers.
Add pickling salt and let set for 1 hour; drain good.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix with squash mixture and heat.
Put into jars.
Cook 15 minutes in hot water bath.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Beat egg yolks in medium size pot and add sugar and flour.
Mix well and add milk, water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add margarine and mix real good. Pour into pie shells.
Make meringue and spread over pies.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple sour cream ring
directions: In a small bowl, combine nuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Grease a spring-form tube pan (9-inch).
In a large bowl, beat butter with 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and all remaining ingredients.
Beat at low speed until blended and raise beating speed to medium and beat 3 minutes.
Spread half of the batter in tube pan; sprinkle 1/3 of nut mixture over it and then spread all apple slices over it.
Spread evenly over the apples the remaining batter and then the nut mixture.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.

title: rhubarb-strawberry mold
directions: Boil rhubarb in water and sugar, stirring until soft.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill at least eight hours.
Serve with fish or meat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in egg until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped Butterfinger chips.
Drop dough by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
Let stand on cookie sheet 2 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: minute steak luzern
directions: Brown steaks in oil 3 minutes on each side in a large skillet. Add onions and broth; cook 1 minute.
Top steaks with cheese; sprinkle with parsley.
Cover.
Cook 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tbsp butter and remove from pan.
Remove fat and bone from steak.
Cut into 2 1/2-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Melt additional 2 tbsp butter in pan.
Toss strips of meat in flour, coating thoroughly.
Brown meat in butter.
Add salt and soup mixture.
Simmer stirring occasionally, until meat is tender, about 1 1/4 hour.
Add mushrooms, onions, and sour cream, heat. Serve over rice or noodles. 6 servings.

title: cheese bake
directions: Mix eggs, tomato sauce, milk and seasonings. Arrange layers of bread, cheese and sauce mixture in greased square pan. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: baked clam spread
directions: Put clams and lemon juice in saucepan and simmer 15 minutes. Drain clams and save liquid.
In saucepan, put liquid from clams, butter and all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Bring to a boil. Add clams and stir.
Add bread crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Empty saucepan into 1-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool and serve warm on crackers.
(Suggest Triscuits.)

title: southern sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and knead thoroughly to blend.
Roll into small walnut-sized balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
It makes 60 to 70 balls.
May be baked and refrigerated, then reheated to serve.

title: creole squash
directions: Cook squash. Drain well. In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Place drained squash in greased shallow casserole.
Pour sauce over this. Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 generously.

title: no bake rice pudding
directions: Combine
milk,	rice
and salt.
Cook for 45 minutes in double boiler,
stirring occasionally.
Beat 2 eggs slightly; add
3/4 cup
sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.	Pour some of the cooked
rice into egg-sugar mixture.
Return to double boiler and
cook	for
5 to
6 more minutes.
Plumped raisins may be added.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and brown thoroughly in margarine. Add soup mix, water and sour cream.
Cook, covered, slowly for 25 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir often and add enough water along to keep moist, but not soupy.
Serve over hot rice.

title: harvard beet cake
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend beets in blender until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with beets to oleo mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into 9 to 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add melted butter, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.
Cool and serve.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add milk and potato soup.
Increase heat to medium, stirring occasionally.
When mixture is hot, add cheese to speed melting.
When creamy, add cooked wild rice.

title: quick vanilla sauce
directions: Mix all items and beat until smooth.
Chill.
If it's too thick, add a little more cream.
Very good over baked apple dumplings or cake desserts.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine and mix all but chocolate chips.
Beat 3 minutes until smooth, then add chips.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, depending on size of pan used.
Cool and sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.

title: cheese and bacon rolls
directions: Use Pepperidge Farm bread (not as greasy). Spread Cheez Whiz on slice of bread.
Cut bread in 4 or 5 slices.
Roll the bread, then put slices of thin bacon around it.
Cook on broiler pan in 350° oven for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread chicken and veggies evenly in pan.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small bowl; pour evenly into pan.
Combine Recip-Ease baking mix and milk in a separate bowl.
Stir until smooth and pour evenly over other ingredients in pan.
Place butter slices on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: fudgy brownie
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda into mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup corn oil.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, egg whites and remaining 1/3 cup corn oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour and vanilla.
Blend completely.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick vegetable oil spray.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, Karo and water.
Mix for 5 minutes on high.
Add pecans and stir.
Cook 4 to 4 1/2 minutes until caramel color.
Put in pan (cookie sheet) and cover with chocolate chips.
Spread while hot.
Sprinkle with nuts.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: friendly frank's fried rice
directions: Cook rice until tender and dry.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain grease from skillet (all but 3 to 4 tablespoons).
Add rice, chopped peppers, onions, scrambled eggs and crumbled bacon.
Let heat over low heat while stirring to mix.
Let cook until peppers and onions are done.
Serve while hot with soy sauce.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil and stir well.
Next add baking powder, flour and salt and stir again.
Last add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake at approximately 350° or less.

title: flat bread
directions: Melt shortening and add to water.
Mix dry ingredients together and stir in water mixture.
Knead slightly before rolling out. Bake in oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add the 10x sugar and coconut flakes; mix with a spoon.
Knead with hands.
Roll into small balls, then roll in cinnamon.
Refrigerate.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Melt butter with sugar and curry powder.
Drain fruit and place in baking dish.
Cover with melted mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with Frito scoops corn chips.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: honey-oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; stir by hand until completely mixed.
Fill 12 paper lined or greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for approximately 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; dot with butter in a well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Keep covered until about the last 5 minutes.
Remove cover until done.

title: monster cookiesdiagonal, iowa
directions: Cream together:
eggs, sugar, butter and brown sugar. Add: vanilla, peanut butter and soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Add: oatmeal, chocolate chips, nuts and M&M's.
Mix well.
Use an ice cream scoop to dip dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: house tea
directions: Brew tea bags according to package instructions.
Combine remaining ingredients with brewed tea in 1-gallon container.
Add water to fill and chill.

title: after-church stew
directions: Place beef in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.
Combine soup and water; pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.
Cream of mushroom soup may be used in place of tomato soup.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add 4 cups rhubarb (frozen should be slightly thawed).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and cook until margarine is melted. Add 2 to 3 drops of hot sauce, if desired.

title: german chocolate upside-down surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly over bottom of greased pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed.
Spoon batter evenly over coconut and pecans.
In another large bowl, combine powdered sugar, margarine and cream cheese; beat until smooth and creamy.
Spoon evenly over batter to within 1-inch of edges.
Bake at 375° for 43 to 53 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.
Invert each square onto individual plates.
Serve warm or cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in large saute pan.
Saute remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Add shrimp to mixture and saute just until the shrimp turn pink.

title: scarparelli
directions: Using 1/2 of oil, saute onions and garlic with wine for about 2 minutes.	Add
sausage.
Cook
on medium until sausage is cooked.
Add chicken and rest
of
oil, the thyme and salt. Cook with cover on for
about
minutes
or
until
cooked, stirring occasionally.
Cook
pasta as desired.
Serve mixture over pasta. Sprinkle with hot peppers.

title: mushroom meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Shape into balls (about 15).
Roll in flour and fry in butter or oil until browned.
Place browned meat balls in casserole dish.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil tomato soup (do not add water).
Take off stove.
Cube cheese and add until smooth.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix 2 things together.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add mayonnaise, celery, grated shrimp and onion.
Oil Jell-O mold. Make 1 day ahead.

title: fruit surprise
directions: Chill all ingredients in refrigerator before using.
Can be mixed at last minute before serving.
All fruit pie fillings can be used as a change.
Put all ingredients into a bowl.
Mix and serve.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil the water, sugar and cornstarch and cook until clear.
Add Jell-O and a few drops of red food coloring.
Place 2 cups of fresh whole strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over and let set for about 5 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions.
Add soup to hamburger.
Put 1/2 Tater Tots in bottom of the pan.
Pour meat mixture over the top of the Tater Tots.
Dot the meat mixture with the rest of the Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on bottom rack of oven at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes. Also makes nice bars by baking in oblong pan.

title: grandmas macaroni and cheese
directions: Use a 2 quart casserole dish, butter sides and bottom.
Make 3 layers using sliced cheese, 1 tbsp flour and pepper, over macaroni. On second layer add the onion to taste.
Ending with layer of cheese, 1 Tbsp flour and salt and pepper on top.
Cover the whole thing with milk.
Be generous.
Bake at 350 for approximately 45 minutes until cheese on top golden brown.

title: praline cookies(bars)
directions: On a large cookie sheet (with sides), place the whole graham crackers to cover the entire pan.
In saucepan, bring brown sugar and butter to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes only.
Add pecans and pour over graham crackers, spreading to the edges of graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Fry bacon slowly in skillet. Drain on paper.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown. Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed, and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely, then cover with drained pineapple.
Sprinkle over cake.

title: creole gumbo(pressure cooker directions)
directions: Heat your pressure cooker.
Brown okra lightly in your ham fat.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and allow steam to escape releasing all your air from cooker.
Add weight. Cook 15 minutes with stem at cook position.
Turn off and allow stem to go back down, open when safe.

title: just peachy pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese, cracker crumbs, liquid from asparagus and 1/4 cup butter.
Grease bowl with butter and save the rest for the top of the casserole.
Place layer of cheese and cracker mixture in baking dish.
Next, a layer of asparagus, then a layer of eggs and pimento.
Cover with can of soup.
Use rest of cracker mixture to cover top and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Work macaroon paste and sugar together until thoroughly blended, using fingertips.
Add unbeaten egg whites, one at a time, and beat until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar, mixed with flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto unglazed paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Brush tops of macaroon with cold water and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Make Early in the Day:
In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir milk, mashed potatoes and 1/2 cup water until well mixed.
Add butter and, over medium heat, heat until very warm (120° to 130°), stirring occasionally.
(Butter does not need to melt completely.) With mixer at low speed, gradually pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat in eggs.
Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat in 1 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter; continue beating 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour (about 3 1/4 cups) to make a soft dough.

title: john's jungle juice
directions: Mix together and put in jar. Drink 2 ounces in the morning and 2 ounces at night. This is good for cholesterol.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry ingredients into creamed mixture, beating well.
Add nuts and coloring.
Bake in small greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: fritos pie
directions: Cook hamburger meat in skillet and drain. Add Ranch Style beans and Spanish rice.
Let boil.
Add grated cheese and Fritos. Mix lightly. Ready to eat.

title: jersey sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine potatoes, butter or margarine and egg; mix thoroughly. Combine and sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to potato mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Yields topping for 1 pot pie.

title: homemade ice cream - "milky way"
directions: Chop candy bars in chunks. Combine with marshmallows and a cup of milk.
Melt in microwave or over hot water until mostly melted. Can have small chunks of candy left.
Mix in other ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer can and finish filling with milk. Freeze as usual.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast dissolved in water and buttermilk.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 425° to 450°.
Can be stored in refrigerator up to 4 days.
These are very good.

title: red-sweet salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Then slowly add a little at a time, 1 cup salad oil.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Mix once in a while or shake container.

title: north carolina rice pudding
directions: Heat cold milk and vanilla, but do not allow to boil.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Place in shallow, buttered baking dish and bake approximately one hour at 350°.
Stir every twenty minutes while baking until set.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Cream eggs and oil until very light.
Add sugar, gradually while beating.
Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour onto jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and spread on peanut butter while still hot. Cool in refrigerator.
When cool, melt chocolate and spread over top.
Cut into bars before chocolate hardens completely.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquids.
Add water to reserved liquid to equal 2 cups.
In a saucepan, bring liquid to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add cold water, onions, horseradish, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set. Stir in beets, celery and olives.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, then vanilla while mixing.
Fold in nuts.
Place on well-greased cookie sheets by spoonfuls.
Spread with spoon until flattened.
Bake in 250° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: madeira cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add the eggs, flour and salt alternatively.
Fold in the rind and juice of lemon.
Put into a prepared 6 inch cake tin and bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.
When cake has been in the oven for 20 minutes, take a slice of citron peel (making sure it is slightly warm) and place on top of cake. Bake for the remainder of the time.

title: italian green beans(low-fat)
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Add water to depth of 1 inch in a large skillet; bring to a boil.
Add beans. Cover, reduce heat and cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain and immediately place in ice water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.
Cook onion and garlic in oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add green beans; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add 2 tablespoons water, sugar, basil and salt; cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove and discard garlic.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: refreshing veggie salad
directions: Cut lettuce and cauliflower fairly fine.
Place in bowl in listed order.
Do not mix.

title: zucchini spice cake
directions: Add wet ingredients (last 6 ingredients) and dry ingredients (first 7 ingredients) together.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch round cake pans for 30 minutes.
Serve with cream cheese or whipped cream.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and oleo.
Cook 12 minutes over medium heat, stirring so it won't stick.
When slightly thick, remove from heat and add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Cool slightly and ice cake.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together over medium heat.
Serve hot in fondue pot with chips or crackers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onions; drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture, then cheese (will make 3 layers) in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: You will need butter flavored cooking spray.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit in colander. Let stand for several hours in order to drain excess juice. In large bowl, combine fruit, sour cream and marshmallows.
Refrigerate prior to serving.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough into 1/4-inch thick circle.
Place single layer of mortadella, Provolone and salami.
Sprinkle Romano cheese, crushed red pepper and oregano.
Roll up like a jelly roll; seal edges and ends.
Place seam side down on a greased cookie sheet. Brush top with olive oil.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut in 1-inch slices and serve.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: ham one-dish meal
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes, onions, carrots and ham; place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Blend together the flour, soup, milk and pepper in saucepan and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture boils.
Pour over vegetables and ham.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: nutmeg sauce
directions: Mix the sugar, nutmeg, flour and salt together in pan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add the vinegar and butter.
Very good with apple desserts.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in alternately with the milk. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately roll in 6 tablespoons butter, then a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: green rice
directions: Mix together.
Put in oblong dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Combine pie filling, brown sugar and cinnamon; add nuts. Spread 1/2 in pie shell.
Chill
remaining
mix.
Pour milk and cream in small mixing bowl.
Add
remainder of pie filling mix. Beat at
lowest speed until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon over apple mixture in pie shell.
Freeze 1 hour or chill 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip if desired.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In separate bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn crisp
directions: Pop corn and put in a large metal pan or bowl.
Place in 200° oven to keep warm.
Mix sugars, syrup and water together in saucepan; bring to a boil and add salt.
Continue to boil until temperature reaches 300°.
Add butter and mix well.
Take off heat and add baking soda which has been mixed with vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour mixture over warm popcorn and mix together.
Pour out on waxed paper.
Spread thin while still hot.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water, until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring until reaches 260 degrees on a candy thermometer (or until a small amount of mixture dropped into cold water forms a hard ball). In mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites. Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds it's shape and becomes slightly dull. Fold in nuts. Drop mixture from tip of buttered spoon onto wax paper.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Soak fruit in water and cover for several hours or overnight. Cook in this water until tender; stir.
Remove from heat.
Mash until smooth.
Add sugar.
Set aside to cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add onion.
Stir in milk and egg.
Fry teaspoonfuls of batter in hot shortening until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with fish or meat. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: sweet and spicy cereal mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice cereal, noodles and pecans. In small saucepan stir together margarine, honey, and pumpkin pie spice.
Cook on low until margarine is melted.
Drizzle over cereal mixture.
Place in oven.
Bake 12 minutes, stirring once. Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Store and serve as needed.

title: bean soup
directions: Clean and rinse beans; soak overnight or longer.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except tomatoes, celery, carrots, potato flakes and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove meat from bone; cut into small pieces and return to soup.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots and potato flakes to thicken.
Stir until blended, then add oil.
Return to heat; simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, pineapple and Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Coat a skillet with nonstick cooking spray; saute the green chilies and onions until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, garlic powder, oregano and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes, or until thick.
Combine chicken and yogurt; place in a shallow 3-quart baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Add tortilla strips on top of chicken mixture; cover with tomato sauce.
Top casserole with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 10 servings.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat butter, Crisco and sugar until light & fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients & add to creamed mixture. Add milk, alternating with dry ingredients. Add vanilla & nuts. Pour into greased 10 inch tube pan. Bake 1 hour & 15 minutes at 350 degrees or until done. I serve with strawberries or glaze.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Brown sausage and onion; drain off fat.
Mix browned sausage and onion with remaining ingredients. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, a little at a time, to form a slightly moist dough.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Turn dough into greased round pan.
For best results, cut an "X" in top and extend down the sides.
Pat lightly with milk before baking.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: You can add more peanut butter if you like.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Add sugar and water to make simple syrup. Bring to boil and cool. Mix lemonade to syrup mixture. Pour about 1 cup of mixture in blender and add egg whites. Blend until frothy. Pour back into other mixture. This makes over 1 gallon of mix. Store in gallon containers in refrigerator (can store up to 3 weeks). Add whiskey when ready to use. ADD AT LEAST 1 FIFTH (or more) of WHISKEY.

title: split pea soup(ertesuppe)
directions: Rinse peas.
Cover with water in large kettle.
Cook until nearly tender.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer until cooked. Dilute with broth if desired.

title: peachy keen cobblerstilwell, kansas
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°.
While oven is heating, melt butter in oven in a 9 X 12-inch baking dish.

title: mozzarella wonders
directions: Cut Mozzarella into cheese stick sizes and place in a Ziploc bag containing the flour and herb seasoning; toss to coat the cheese.
Remove cheese from bag and gently shake to remove excess flour.
Next dip in the egg and roll in the bread crumbs, coating well.
In a 2-quart saucepan or deep fryer, heat oil until hot. Fry cheese sticks about 30 seconds, or until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Do ahead.
Coat cheese sticks but do not cook.
Freeze, then fry as needed.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze in 1-gallon ice cream freezer.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt oleo in oven. Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over oleo in baking dish.
Pour fruit over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake in medium degree oven until bubbly and starts to brown on top.

title: easy caramel corn
directions: Spray Pam
on
sides
and bottom of 1 large brown paper grocery bag.
Fill
1/3 to 1/2 full with popped corn (unpopped kernels removed).
Melt the butter in 4 cup glass measure cup. Add to
butter
the
brown sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High 2 minutes covered with wax paper.
This mixture will need to be stirred
down frequently.
Stir in baking soda and cook on
High another 2 minutes, stirring mixture down frequently. To bag of popped corn, add syrup mixture, stirring constantly. Fold bag
and microwave 1 minute.
Shake bag and bake another 1/2 minute. Remove bag and split one side open to allow corn to cool.

title: 4 layer sundae dessert
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Put into 12 or 13-inch pan (cover bottom of pan).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool before spreading next ingredient.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Mix together.
Spread on top of nut mixture.
Mix pudding.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip (small container); sprinkle top with nuts (crushed).
Refrigerate until ready to eat. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
In a cake pan, sprinkle Oreos over bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 of pudding, spreading evenly over cookies, then spread 1/2 Cool Whip over pudding.
(Repeat the same steps until mixture is all gone.)
Garnish with crumbled cookies. Chill before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Add first 4 ingredients all together and top with cheese.
Use cornbread mix, mixed as directed on package or make your own.

title: 1 gallon celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with a spoon.
Then beat with electric beater until desired thickness.

title: italian vegetable medley
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine everything, except cherry tomatoes.
Cover and cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes, until zucchini is almost done.
Add cherry tomatoes, cover and cook on High for 1 minute, until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: *May use one bag, each frozen.

title: powder puff balls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Grease a 12-muffin pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a loaf. Place in greased 9 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Pour off juice.
Bake about 10 minutes longer.
Place on platter and cover with sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco pizza pan dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Spread this mixture on a lined waxed paper pizza pan, then spread taco sauce on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then put lettuce, tomatoes, mild cheese and black olives and then sprinkle green onions on top. Get you a big bag of Doritos and start dipping in.
If you don't like all the ingredients listed, just use the ones you do like.

title: micro minestrone
directions: In a 2-quart microwave casserole, mix oil and vegetables, except tomatoes.
Cover loosely with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quick nut cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with the sugar until mixture is white.
Add oil, lemon juice, and cognac and when well blended, mix in the flour and baking soda.
This mixture will be loose.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Now beat egg whites with the cup of sugar until it is stiff.
Mix in the nuts; after 10 minutes, remove pan from oven and pour on the nut mixture.
Replace in oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into squares when cold.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, green pepper, onion and salt and let set 4 hours.
Squeeze juice out with hand, not too dry.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to boil; add relish and boil 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal for storage.

title: roll-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
Dough will be stiff. Blend last dough by hand.
Do not chill.
Divide dough into 2 balls.
On floured surface, roll each ball into a circle about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out cookies and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Bake on top rack.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and onion rings.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle over top grated cheese and onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Can be prepared the day before. Add cheese and onion rings just before baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and allow to stand for a while before serving.

title: shredded mangos
directions: Simmer until tender.
Place in quart cans and seal.

title: cheddar chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the chicken, in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with the chicken breasts and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple chunks in bottom of casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and grated cheese.
Pour over pineapple chunks.

title: baked pancake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until very light.
Add salt, flour and milk. Beat well. Thoroughly rub bottom and sides of a 10-inch cast-iron or heavy skillet with butter.

Pour batter into skillet. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 5 minutes more or until set. Remove pancake from skillet and place on a large hot platter. Dust with confectioners sugar and garnish with lemon.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: You will need one straw.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Bake patties in medium oven, enough to thaw and heat them. Pour tomato sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay patties over sauce.
Sprinkle some cheese over top.
Add more sauce to cover.
Sprinkle spices (basil, oregano and parsley) over top and add rest of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti and a salad.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 plastic cups (8 ounces).

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Combine juice, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour hot syrup over peaches.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, vanilla and sugar.
Add flour. Drop 1/2 tsp. mixture on cookie sheet.
Press with thumbs.
Fill with small amount of jelly.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed trout
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent, stirring often to avoid browning.
Mix stuffing mix according to package directions and add onion, shrimp, parsley and sour cream.
Fill cavity of trout with mixture and place on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Brush with butter.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature and combine.
Cut onion in fourths and chop in blender.
(I add a little water, then strain the onion after it is minced.)
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/4 cup parsley to cheese mixture; mix well.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in remaining nuts and parsley. Wrap balls tightly and chill.
These can be frozen.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Treat griddle with margarine. Ladle about 2 tablespoons mixture for each cake on greased griddle. Cook slowly until browned lightly on both sides.

title: sweet and pungent shrimp
directions: Cook fresh shrimp in boiled salted water over moderate heat (about 250°) for 5 minutes.
For frozen shrimp, follow package directions.
Drain and cool in cold water.
If in shell, clean and devein.

title: homemade manicotti
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand 1 hour at room temperature. Using a 6-inch nonstick saute pan, heat scant teaspoon oil.
Wipe with paper towel to coat pan evenly.
Spread 1 tablespoon batter over pan; tilt to cover surface and cook until dry, not brown.
Do not turn; flip onto clean dish towel to cool.
Do not stack.
When finished making crepes, mix together the filling.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Soak raisins and nuts in water while mixing cake.
Mix flour, sugar, spices, salt and soda.
Make a hole in middle of mixture. Add applesauce, eggs and oil. Mix for 5
minutes.
Drain raisins and nuts. Dredge in flour.
Add to cake mixture.
Pour into greased lined tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° and 15 minutes at 375°.
When done, leave in pan.
Cover tightly until cool, preferably overnight.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over chops.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add syrup, melted butter and vanilla.
Place pecans into pie pan on unbaked pie shell.
Pour syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 1 hour at 375°.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve immediately or chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken squares
directions: Use 1/2 cup mix per square.
Fold over; brush top with butter. Sprinkle with crushed seasoned croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put the rice, milk, salt and butter in double boiler.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Mix with milk and rice. Return to heat 1 minute.
Cool and add vanilla.

title: crab casserole
directions: Make the white sauce:
Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour and mix to blend.
Gradually add preheated milk.
Mix well; let cool slightly.
Fold in crabmeat, breadcrumbs (no crust), mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add mixture to a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Sprinkle top slightly with seafood seasoning.
Layer the top with desired amount of grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until it just begins to bubble and edges begin to brown.

title: billy's pizza dish
directions: Cook meat and onion in oil.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup juice. Stir into meat.
Add rest of tomatoes and spices.
Cool 15 minutes. Cook noodles and drain.
Grease casserole; layer noodles, meat and cheese.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.

title: p b fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan and stir over medium heat until mixture reaches a soft boil.
Soft boil, while stirring, for 10 minutes.
Remove mixture from heat and quickly stir in peanut butter.
Immediately pour into a 9 x 9-inch glass dish that has been lightly coated with cooking spray.
After fudge has cooled for 5 to 10 minutes, cut into squares and leave in pan to finish cooling.

title: chipped beef and chicken
directions: Cook and cut-up chicken strips.
Boil soup, sour cream and cheese in a pot.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Cut up slices of chipped beef and add to soup mixture.
Add chicken to mixture and pour over rice in casserole dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: c. w.'s broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Place broccoli into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine soup, mayonnaise, melted Cheez Whiz and onion in a small bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over broccoli.
Spread soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Optional:
May add 1 cup cooked, diced chicken or ham.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add sugar, butter, salt and slightly beaten egg yolks to hot potatoes, then add milk and flavoring. Fold in the egg whites which have been stiffly beaten.
The mixture should be fairly thin.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: okra fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add dry mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add to okra.
Spoon by heaping teaspoonfuls into deep fryer and fry until crisp.
Serve with melted butter.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Stir well.
Add eggs.
Stir; do not beat.
Add Pet milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 13 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: You can use low-fat of all ingredients.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, soda, cocoa, flour and buttermilk.
Add spices.
Add raisins, nuts, jam and margarine; mix well.
Add 3 eggs separately. Mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan; bake until done.
Remove from oven and cool before frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: candied pecans
directions: Warm nuts in nonstick baking pan. Combine all ingredients except nuts in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes. Time it. Pour over warm nuts. Stir to coat all nuts. Pour onto cookie sheet to cool. Nuts will break apart when cool.

title: sour cream bundt cake
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Bake in bundt pan at 350° till done.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve as dip with raw veggies.

title: extra good potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in salted water.
When soft, rub through strainer.
There should be 2 1/2 cups.
Scald the milk with onion, remove the onion and slowly whisk the milk into the potatoes. Melt half of the butter and add the flour, salt, celery salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir until well mixed, then stir into the hot soup.
Boil for 1 minute, strain and add the remaining butter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and butter.
Combine noodles, tuna fish and onion salt in buttered casserole dish.
Mix in grated cheese and soup, diluted with 1/2 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fried mozzarella
directions: Cut Mozzarella into
large
squares.
Roll in flour and dip in eggs which	have
been
seasoned
with salt and pepper. Roll in bread crumbs and then in eggs again.
Finally, roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine the hamburger, Lipton soup mix, bread crumbs and eggs.
Form into meatballs and layer then in a 9 x 13 pan.
In another bowl, combine the water, sauerkraut, brown sugar, cranberry sauce and chili sauce.
Mix well and pour over the meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onions, and garlic if you wish, in a little water until they are transparent.
Place these in a bowl.
Cook in a small amount of water and watch while cooking so that there is little liquid left.
Do not drain, the little juice has a lot of flavor and good stuff.
In the same pan, cook the meat until it is done; do not overcook.
Add salt and pepper if you wish.
Put the onions in and a few tablespoons of a combination of the sauces.
I use about half as much tomato sauce to the enchilada sauce because I want it to have the flavor but, not to hot.
So, you decide what combination you would like.
Dice the olives and grate the cheese. Heat the sauce.
Dip the tortillas, one at a time, in the hot sauce and line the 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put half of the meat and onions on top of the tortillas, grated cheese on top of the meat and a few tablespoons of sauce on the cheese.
Dip more tortillas and place another layer on top of the first.
Cut tortillas before dipping when you want to cover a small area, such as corners. Continue with the layers of meat, cheese and sauce.
Sprinkle the olives on the top or put them inside.
I have also used drained canned corn along with the meat.
This is optional.
Also I use the white corn tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, covered.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Combine mixes, soda, oil and eggs.
Beat well for 2 minutes. Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Saute onion, salt and mustard in 1/2-stick margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cook until bubbly.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine meat with remaining ingredients.
Bake in covered pan at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stick fork in meat to check when tender.
Remove meat when done and cool.
Slice thin.
Put meat back in juice and warm to serve.

title: bavarian apple tart
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla with flour and mix well.
Spread in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cover bottom and 2-inches up sides.

title: olive surprises
directions: Mix and chill well; roll in balls around olives. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If you wish, make dough as instructed, cut with small cutter size of a quarter and place pecan half on top. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Mix together and chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: fruit slush
directions: Cook 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 cup water until it boils.
Set aside to cool.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat margarine (or butter) and oil in Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan.
Add chicken and brown well.
Add tomatoes (chopped), chicken broth, onion, parsley, salt, pepper, bay leaf and garlic (minced).
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes.
Add rice and cook 10 minutes, stir occasionally.
Add peas and cook 10 minutes longer or until done and all the liquid is absorbed.

title: chocolate chip pops
directions: You will also need 8 (3 ounce) paper cups and 8 wooden sticks.

title: quick crabmeat spread
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Place cream cheese on serving piece.
Add crabmeat on top.
Then pour cocktail sauce over top of crabmeat. Serve with crackers.

title: grand marnier cheese cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon Grand Marnier.
Spoon into prepared crust in pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature on wire rack.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Remove pan sides.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.
Serves 10 to 12 persons.

title: teresa's chicken and dumpling pie
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
In bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken and remaining ingredients.
Blend in noodles. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese buns
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Spread on top and bottom of bun.
Add 1 piece of ham and 1 piece of Velveeta cheese.
Wrap each sandwich in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots almost done, then add all other vegetables and simmer 30 minutes.
Season well with salt, pepper and any other seasoning that you enjoy.
Before quite done, add some instant potatoes just enough to thicken broth slightly.

title: hesenpfeffer
directions: Cut cleaned rabbit into serving pieces.
Place them in a crock or jar and cover them with the vinegar and water.
Add the seasonings and soak rabbit for 2 days.
Remove the rabbit and roll in flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Gradually add 1 cup of pickling solution.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Thicken with flour the liquid that remains and season to taste.

title: luau sausages
directions: Heat jelly, chili sauce, lemon juice and mustard.
Add sausage and pineapple.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve in small crock-pot with toothpicks.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let cucumbers and onions stand in salt water overnight.
(Use a large enamel pan and just cover cucumbers and onions with water.) Make a syrup of vinegar, turmeric, mustard seed and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions which have been removed from the salt water and drained completely dry.
Cook on medium heat. Leave in just long enough for it to simmer and just start to bubble.
Remove from fire and put in sterilized jars.
When jars are filled, add 1/4 teaspoon of powdered alum to each quart; seal.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Cook hamburger; drain.
Mix together.
Add chili powder and tomato catsup.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 3 minutes.

title: lo-cal salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: country ham balls
directions: Combine ham, crumbs, egg and milk.
Form mixture into 1 inch balls.
Place close together in small baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 18.
May be refrigerated or frozen, then heated at serving time.

title: english toffee
directions: Stir constantly until hard crack stage.
Place on buttered jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Add 10 plain Hershey candy bars. Spread melted chocolate and add crushed fine pecans.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening and sugar; cool.
Add yeast, beaten eggs, flour and salt.
Let rise until doubled; push down. Roll out small amount; cover with softened butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar.
Roll the dough and cut into small slices. Put into pans to rise.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, except pecans.
Lightly fold in pecans.

title: scrumptious green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in pot.
Cook on top of stove, boiling first.
Then simmer for 5 - 10 minutes.

title: okra succotash
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat until okra is done. Serve over rice, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix lemonade and limeade according to can directions.
Chill in pitchers.
Place all juice, 7-Up and Squirt in a punch bowl. Add fresh lemon and lime slices to bowl.
Serve.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat.
Simmer until potatoes are done. Add milk, butter and clams.
Bring back to slow simmer.
