Let stew until flavor is absorbed into potatoes and until done.

title: paprikash krumpkle
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick (as many as needed). Add paprika to color!
Saute onion in butter and potatoes.
Cover with water and add hot dogs.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to directions. Let cool; split layers in half.

title: tomato relish
directions: *Tie in small white cloth where you can remove after this is done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine with mixer.
Blend in flour slowly. Stir in Rice Krispies and cayenne pepper.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and butter; mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 of the flour; beat until no lumps. Gradually add remaining flour.
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
Take half of the dough; roll out to a circle 12 inches in diameter. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Leave edges a little thicker than middle.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Brush the tops with salad oil.

title: aunt gloria's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken with onion.
Debone chicken; save broth and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients with 3 cups broth.
Pour mixture over deboned chicken that has been put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: meat and cheese ball
directions: Cut meat into small squares.
Soften the cream cheese and add the Accent, Worcestershire sauce, onions and 1 package of meat. Mix well and shape into a ball.
Put second package of meat on outside of the ball.

title: master mix biscuits
directions: Stir milk into Master Mix until flour is moistened.
Knead 15 strokes on lightly floured board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: pecan cluster cookies
directions: Beat egg white and sugar until mixture is light and sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Toss the nuts in this until they are coated.
Drop by spoonful onto greased and floured cookie sheet, dropping about 3 pecans to each cookie.
Preheat oven to 350°
for 10 minutes.
Put cookie sheet in oven and turn off heat.
Let cookies sit in oven for 50 minutes.
Store in tins.

title: frozen salad
directions: Pour 1/2 cup fruit juice over marshmallows.
Let stand while combining other ingredients.
Then fold together and freeze.

title: spicy roll-ups
directions: Cut steak into 6 pieces about 8 x 4-inches.
Pound with meat hammer.
Combine rice
and
raisins,
place
in center of each piece of meat.
Roll
up
and
tuck in ends.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except gingersnaps.
Cover,
simmer 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Remove
cloves
and bay leaf.
Add gingersnaps. Cook 15 minutes more.
Stir now and then.

title: grandma's spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; fry hamburger.
Drain noodles and hamburger.
Put into rectangle pan (sheet cake size); add noodles,
hamburger and ketchup.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Put in oven for 10 minutes; take out.
Put biscuits on top of mixture; small pat of butter on top of biscuits. Important:
Reduce oven temperature to 250°.
Put spaghetti with biscuits back in oven.
Bake biscuits until done, 15 to 30 minutes.

title: libby chowning's frozen salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with pinch of salt in 1 cup boiling water. Add mayonnaise and juice from pineapple and maraschino cherries. Set in refrigerator and let cool until thickens.
Whip cream; add bananas and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Add chopped cherries, pineapple and a few chopped nuts.
Pour into lightly oiled loaf pan and freeze.

title: chicken wingdings
directions: In a saucepan, mix the syrup, catsup, soy sauce, mustard, ginger and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil; cook over medium heat about 6 minutes.
Cut wings in halves at joint.
Place skin side down on foil-lined jelly roll pan.
Pour sauce over chicken, coating evenly.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Turn chicken skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes, spooning sauce occasionally.
Serve hot with remaining sauce or serve cold.
Makes 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Pour 1 cup of sauce into bottom of 12 x 18-inch microwavable dish and spread evenly.
Top with remaining ingredients in this order:
noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce, half of Ricotta, half of Mozzarella and 3 tablespoons of Parmesan.
Repeat the process and cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover dish with plastic wrap in which you have poked several small holes.
Microwave on High 25 to 30 minutes.
(Microwave cooking time may vary.)
Turn once.
Allow lasagna to stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned evenly.
Add water, reduce to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Drain, allow sausage to stand at room temperature until cool enough to handle.
Heat oil in 5-quart pot.
Cook onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Stir in beef stock, tomatoes, carrot, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes.
Cut sausages into thin slices, add to pot, simmer 10 minutes.
Bring soup to a boil, add zucchini and tortellini.
Reduce heat to medium-high and gently boil 7 minutes or when pasta is tender.
Serve with sprinkle of Parmesan.
Serves 6.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce, slice onions, slice water chestnuts and layer in order given.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: freezer meat balls
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in breadcrumbs, onion and salt. Add ground beef; mix well.	Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Bake meatballs, half at a time, in large shallow pan; cool.
Arrange cooled meatballs in single layer on baking sheet so edges do not touch.
Freeze until firm. Using 24 meatballs per package, wrap meatballs in freezer bags.	Seal, label and freeze.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In large bowl, blend sugar, oleo and chocolate; add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight. Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar, coating lightly.
Then shape into balls.
Place on greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart; flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheets onto wire racks to cool.

title: spareribs-cabbage 'n kraut("for crock-pot")
directions: Sprinkle spareribs with salt and pepper.
Brown spareribs in heavy skillet or broiler pan.
Drain.
Put sauerkraut, cabbage, onion and apple in crock-pot.
Add browned ribs.
Add caraway seed or dill weed to water and pour over all.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (or high for 4 to 5 hours; stir several times during cooking when using high only).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Slice strawberries.
Blend whipped topping in gelatin.
Then fold in cake cubes and strawberries. Spoon in 10-inch tube pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Makes 10 cups of 12 to 15 servings.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a baked pie shell. Freeze for several hours before cutting.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes well and dry them. Prick potato skins with fork.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out potato without breaking skin.
Mash the potatoes with butter, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Fill potato skins.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in baking dish.
Return to the oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Slice squash slightly thin.
Blanch squash and drain; set aside.
Beat eggs as if for an omelet.
Add cheese, pepper and onion; blend.
Spray glass baking dish with Pam cooking spray.
Place a row of squash in dish.
Pour a covering of egg mixture.
Add remaining squash and cover with remaining egg mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Bring green beans to a boil; drain off water.
Mix in mushroom soup and put in a casserole dish.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until onion rings are brown.

title: fresh veggie appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Unroll dough into 4 rectangles. Press onto bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish to form crust. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown; cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and cook until onions are tender.
Put into casserole dish alternately with soups and Tater Tots.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.
Top with cheese and heat until the cheese is melted.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring to boil the ham bone in a soup pot. Boil for about 10 minutes. Remove bone. Add veggies. Boil for about 20 minutes until tender, not soft; stir often. Stir in Velveeta; cook on medium heat for another 5 minutes. Mix cornstarch with about 4 tablespoons water. Mix in, stirring constantly. This will cause the soup to thicken. Add more if not thick enough.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice to boiling; pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved, then cool.
Beat cream cheese with 2 tablespoons cream until smooth; add jello.
Beat until partially thick.
Fold in mashed pears and whipping cream.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: To very soft and creamed shortening, add other ingredients and mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Chill for about an hour.

title: layer salad
directions: Use a big salad bowl.
Make in order given in layers.
Do not mix.
Make at least one day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stays crisp. Toss before serving.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs with 3 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Melt butter.
Mix with crumbs and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes and cool.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed (except butter).
Mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Let sit in fridge until well chilled.
Roll into small balls and bake on cookie sheets (greased) at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 60 to 80 balls.

title: mexican dip
directions: Dice onion; brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Mix in taco seasoning, refried beans, kidney beans, jalapeno relish and green chilies.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Slice black olives and green onions on top of cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tomato, lettuce, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: hot reuben sandwiches
directions: To make dressing:
Combine mayonnaise, chili sauce and dill pickle in small bowl.
Spread top and bottom half of rolls with dressing.
Place the corned beef on the bottom half of each roll. Top each with sauerkraut and 1 slice of cheese.
Cover with the top half of the roll.
Tear off 4 pieces of aluminum foil; wrap each sandwich securely.
Heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: apricot cake
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites.
Mix cake mix, yolks, oil and apricot nectar at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Beat egg whites until
stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange crush cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Add Orange Crush alternately with sifted flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hot cocoa for a crowd
directions: In a large kettle, combine sugar, cocoa, salt and warm water. Mix well. Add boiling water and boil for 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in hot milk.
Very good! Great for sled riding parties! Yields 100 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, onion and green pepper in blender and pour over beans.
Chill before serving.
Flavor improves overnight or longer.

title: cream puff
directions: Bring water and butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Cook on low heat until the mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute). Remove from heat, add eggs and beat until smooth.
Drop by 1/4 c. on ungreased baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 35-40 minutes.
Cool and add filling.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients but whipping cream together.
Beat whipping cream until stiff and add to fruit mixture.
Freeze at least 3 hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring sugars, molasses, water and vinegar to boil; boil until forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and soda.
Stir mixture into popcorn and form into balls.

title: christmas cookies(cutouts)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Alternate cups of milk.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for approximately 6 to 8 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll small portion into balls; place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Saute onion
in butter until tender.
Add hamburg, A.1. sauce and salt.
Brown lightly.
Stir in soup and beans.	Pour mixture into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with mounds of mashed potatoes. Bake in a
oven for 25 minutes or until potatoes are lightly brown.
Serve with A.1.
steak sauce.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix together.
Freeze in Ziploc bags (each about the size of an orange).
Makes enough for 18 single crust pies.

title: kim's corn casserole
directions: Combine the two kinds of corn. Stir in sour cream and beaten eggs. Add sugar and melted butter. Stir in corn muffin mix. Pour batter into ungreased casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with cheese. Return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening, egg and vanilla.
Work in coconut and oats; roll into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt.

title: skillet date cookies
directions: Put dates, margarine and sugar in skillet.
Cook over low flame for 5 minutes.
Stir in beaten egg.
Allow to cool a few minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
When cool enough to handle, roll into balls, then in powdered sugar or flaked coconut.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Chop dates, cherries, pineapple and nuts; combine in a very large bowl.
Add 1/4 cup of the flour, tossing to coat evenly. Set aside.

title: turkey and vegetable salad
directions: Wash and slice potatoes. Cook until tender. Drain potatoes after cooking and place in a large salad bowl. Drain beans.
Add beans, turkey and celery to the salad bowl.
In another small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except celery leaves. Toss dressing with turkey and vegetables just before serving. Garnish with celery leaves. Serves 24.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, egg and sugar together.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Blend in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Roll into balls, 1-inch in size, or you may drop by a teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with a bottom of a glass, that has been dipped into sugar.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: honeycomb toffee brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet with butter.
Combine sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat without stirring until 280° (about 20 minutes).
Stir down and return to heat until 295°. Remove and stir in baking soda.
Pour onto baking sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over brittle.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, add diced apples and pour into oblong pan, 13 x 9-inch.
(Stir this up with spoon.
Don't use mixer.)

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Blend milk and lime juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put into pie shell.
Chill.

title: no rise angel biscuits # 1
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Blend shortening and flour until evenly distributed.
In separate bowl, mix soda, sugar and buttermilk.
Stir yeast and water in with buttermilk.
Pour this mixture in with flour and mix well.
Roll out and cut or pat by hand to desired size.
Place in greased pan and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, rice, broccoli and seasonings.
Turn into greased greased 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 mins.
Meanwhile, beat egg yolks till thick and lemon-colored.
Add cheese.
Beat egg whites till soft peaks form.
Fold in egg yolks.
Remove casserole from oven, stir and spread egg mixture over top.
Bake 15 mins. longer till golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix in 1-quart casserole.
Slowly stir in rice mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool at least 1 hour before serving.

title: beer simmered pork chops
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
In a separate bowl mix soup, mushrooms, beer and onion soup mix.
Blend well.
Add to skillet and lower heat. Allow chops and sauce to simmer, covered, over low heat for about 50 minutes. Cook rice as directed on package.
Serve pork chops and sauce over rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt syrup, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies and cornflakes.
Pour in an 8-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour. Add 1/4 cup butter with pudding, milk and powdered sugar.
Spread on top.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk. At once, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven (475°) for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean. Cool on rack.
Serve cool or chill.
(To avoid spills, fill at oven.)

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Cook, covered, on top of stove until carrots and potatoes are tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour or bake at 350° in covered casserole dish for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and oleo to a boil.
Cook to medium soft ball stage when dropped in water (243°), stirring all the time. Then immediately add Hip-O-Lite, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until all is melted and gets real thick.
Pour in buttered pan and cut when cool.

title: congealed shrimp salad
directions: Heat tomato soup and water in a sauce pan with salt, Tabasco sauce, pepper, and garlic powder.
Crumble packages of cream cheese into hot soup mixture.
Beat with wire ship until cream cheese is blended with soup.
Dissolve plain gelatin with cool water and pour into soup mixture.
Put shrimp, celery, green pepper, onion and green olives in a bowl.
Pour soup mixture into bowl with chopped ingredients.
Blend.
Chill until firm.

title: special salad
directions: Layer alternately first lettuce, peas, carrots, onions, celery and bacon.
Dot with mayonnaise.
Continue to layer until all vegetables are used.
Let stand few hours to marinate.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Cook carrots and onion in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserve liquid.
Melt butter, blend in flour and gradually add reserved liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place vegetables in buttered dish.
Add sauce and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix together hot water and jello well. Add remaining ingredients. Let set firm.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover. Refrigerate overnight. Serve over lettuce, crackers or pita bread halves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken and cut into small pieces.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package; spread on bottom of baking dish (large, glass baking dish).
Spread chicken over top of stuffing.
Beat together soups and milk.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Do not cover.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, setting aside.
Mix the dry ingredients in the order given, cutting in the shortening as you normally do for biscuits or pie dough.
Stir in the buttermilk and the yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly and the dough is ready to refrigerate or roll out into biscuits.
When you are ready to make biscuits, turn the dough out onto a floured board and knead lightly as for regular biscuits.
Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter, placing them in a greased pan.
Let dough rise slightly before baking at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until done.
If dough is cold, let it set out a little longer.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar and melted butterscotch chips; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Spread batter evenly in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden and set.
Let cool in pan.

title: fluffy gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well. Add molasses and beat until creamy. Add melted shortening, beat, add vanilla and buttermilk and continue beating.

title: heavenly steaks in wine
directions: Rub steaks on both sides with cornstarch; sprinkle with garlic. Heat the butter in a skillet and brown steaks quickly on both sides.
Reduce heat.
Saute steaks until done to your liking, about 4 minutes both sides for rare, about 7 to 9 minutes for well done. Remove steaks, keep warm.
Add green onions to skillet and saute on medium-high until soft but not browned.
Add beef broth and wine. Bring to a boil and add salt and pepper to taste desired.
Add butter in small amount at a time, whisking constantly until sauce is smooth (1 teaspoon cornstarch with a teaspoon water to make sauce smoother).
Pour sauce over steaks, sprinkle with some extra onions.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, butter and syrup.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add pecans and stir well.
Pour in frozen pie crust.
Do not allow pie crust to thaw.
Place in oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then lower oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook until thick.
Perfect for chicken, shrimp, pork chops or just over rice.

title: herbed rolls(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Melt butter and herbs.
Cut rolls into quarters and dip into herb butter.
Place pieces into pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: gingerbread
directions: In small bowl, add 2 teaspoons lemon juice and 1/2 cup skimmed milk to make sour milk; set aside.
Beat egg and sugar or molasses until fluffy.
Mix milk, margarine, sifted flour, baking soda and spices together.
Add egg and sugar; beat until smooth.
Bake in an 8-inch pan (greased) at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O together as directed on box. Set in the refrigerator and let begin to jell. When Jell-O has begun to jell, add other ingredients and put in ring mold. Return to the refrigerator.

title: french green beans
directions: Mix beans, soup, salt, pepper, milk and 1/2 cup onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until soup starts bubbling. Remove from oven; put other 1/2 of onions over the top and return to oven for a few minutes (uncovered).
(Onions on top will burn if not watched.)

title: easy pan burrito casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix tomato paste and enchilada sauce mix according to directions on back of sauce package.
Add 1/2 of sauce to beef and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cream together and add apples.
Beat well, adding flour slowly.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cornflake chews
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over medium heat.
Heat until mixture bubbles and sugar dissolves (approximately 5 minutes).
Add cornflakes, stirring so each flake is covered.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Wait until completely cooled, and put into storage container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend soup, flour and sour cream in a bowl.
Stir in broccoli, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole 3/4 cup herb season stuffing mix and 2 tablespoons butter, melted.
Put around edge of casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate several hours before serving. Makes a bunch.

title: no-cholesterol orange cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add corn oil, orange rind and juice.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth.
In a small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites into flour mixture.
Turn into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Grease a 10 inch skillet or a 2 qt. baking dish. Cook sausage and onion until brown and onion is tender. Beat eggs in large mixing bowl. Add cornmeal, corn, milk and oil. Mix well. Pour half of cornmeal mixture into prepared pan, sprinkle evenly with sausage mixture and cheese. Pour remaining cornmeal mixture over sausage and cheese.

title: hamburger pizza pie
directions: Put hamburger in a 9-inch pie pan and pat it to fit.
Cover with tomatoes and some chopped onions.
Sprinkle with basil, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Delicious served with tossed green salad and French bread.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail and cream cheese, then add oranges, coconut and pecans.
Chill thoroughly.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Beat.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in sour cream.
Put half in a greased Bundt pan.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Pour half over batter.
Add batter and remainder of crumb mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Melt butter.
Mix brown sugar, butter and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Add milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Mix; add blueberries to mixture.
Stir only until blended.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full (greased muffin tins).
Bake in a 375° to 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: foolproof italian bread
directions: Heat water, sugar and salt until it feels very warm on wrist. Add yeast and let sit for a few minutes until yeast works.
Pour into large bowl or pot.
Add in flour, saving some out for kneading process.
After flour is mixed in, dump onto floured board or counter and knead until elastic.
Knead in flour as needed.
Let rise in pot until doubled.
Punch down and shape into three loaves.
Let rise 1/2 hour on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and rub butter over top.
This works great when sliced for individual pizzas.

title: white jello
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water.
While this cools, cream sugar and cream cheese.
Then beat in lemon juice, milk and vanilla.
Add cooled gelatine to the cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and put in greased jello mold.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure flour by dipping-level-pour method or by sifting.
Combine all ingredients and blend well. Roll on floured cloth-covered board to 1/4-inch.
Cut with 1 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until set, but not brown.
Cool and frost cookies with any topping you like.

title: orange julius
directions: Grind ice cubes in blender.
Add milk, orange juice, vanilla and sugar.
Blend well.

title: diet lovers potato cream cheese casserole
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and cheese, beating until well blended. Stir in egg, onion and parsley.
Spoon into well-greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flavorings.
Add 7-Up and flour alternately, beating well.
Bake in tube cake pan that has been greased and floured with bottom lined with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Put in airtight container.
Will last and freezes well.

title: potato salad
directions: Blend with French's mustard.
Blend to taste.
Top with sliced eggs and paprika.

title: mexican perch
directions: Wipe fillets with damp cloth and lay on cookie sheet.
Blend other ingredients and spread on fish.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix milk with pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Then layer: 1 layer graham crackers, 1 layer pudding, 1 layer graham crackers, 1 layer pudding, etc.
End with graham crackers.
Spread with chocolate frosting.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: microwave split pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium. Microwave until vegetables are tender and soup is thickened, 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times during cooking.

title: poached salmon with caper sauce
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Rinse the fish and pat dry with paper towels.
In a 10-inch skillet, combine chicken broth, wine and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Place fish in skillet. Place lemon slices atop dish.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove fish and lemon.
Keep fish warm.
Discard lemon.
Gently boil broth mixture, uncovered, until reduced to 3/4 cup (about 2 minutes). Stir together water and cornstarch.
Stir into broth mixture.
Stir in capers.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Divide zucchini among 4 individual plates. Arrange salmon and cover with sauce.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour; mix well and add pecan meats.
Form small balls or rolls 1 1/2 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until delicately browned.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: company potatoes
directions: Melt oleo; saute onion and pepper.
Mix sour cream with grated Cheddar cheese and mix all with potatoes.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle over top the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Fry sausage and mushrooms; break into bite size pieces.
Put bread cubes into an 8 x 12-inch glass pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 cups of milk and dry mustard.
Pour over cheese.
Layer sausage and mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: beef-rice skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.
Add more liquid, if needed.
When done, sprinkle cheese over top. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: teenie weenies
directions: Boil for 10 minutes .
Chill.
Pour over peaches. Refrigerate.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Chill. Roll into 1 inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar. Serve chilled.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and place in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels, 1 (6 ounce) package.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients about 5 minutes.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake
at
for 45 minutes or until tests done. Cool for
minutes before turning out.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients with a spoon or fork by gradually adding one at a time.
Once generally mixed, knead all ingredients with hands.
Press into a loaf baking pan; flatten out top.
Top with bottle of chili sauce.
Bake at least one hour at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and set aside.
In large bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: low fat barbecue chicken
directions: Put all together into electric frying pan. Cook at medium heat until sauce is thick and chicken is tender.

title: hog maw salad
directions: Cook hog maws until tender.
Take hog maws out of pot and let cool.
Dice hog maws with scissors (they cut better).
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, granulated sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: christmas dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough turkey broth to make dressing.

title: microwave orange glazed carrots
directions: Set power level at High.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine carrots and orange juice; heat, covered, for 7 to 8 1/2 minutes, or until carrots are tender, stirring once.
Stir in remaining ingredients; let stand, covered, 3 minutes before serving.

title: easy nacho avocado dip
directions: Mix ingredients; spread on plate.
Top with chopped tomatoes and green onion.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce in large mixing bowl.
Mix until blended.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in a lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon evenly over loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: mexican rice(24 servings)
directions: Heat grease.
Add rice to brown, stirring.
Add onions; cook until they are golden (5 minutes).
Add tomato juice, tomatoes, stock, hot sauce and salt.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until rice is tender.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Prepare tomatoes, cutting out stems.
Pan-boil approximately 1 minute to loosen skins.
Peel and cut into small pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wipe mushroom caps with a damp cloth and arrange in a shallow baking dish, hollow side up.
Chop stems (there will be about a cup) and mix with pecans, butter or margarine, garlic and some pepper.
Mix everything (except caps and cream) together and heap into mushroom caps.
Pour heavy cream over mushrooms and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, basting one or two times with the cream in the dish.

title: turkey quiche
directions: Make stuffing according to box and press in baking dish forming a crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Combine meat and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Sprinkle meat and cheese over hot crust.
Pour egg and milk mixture on top. Drop temperature down to 350°.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: oreo turkey
directions: Frost top of Oreo with chocolate frosting.
Place Hershey's Kiss on center for turkey face.
Add red hot at base of Kiss for gobbler and 5 candy corn pieces around the Kiss for feathers. Makes about 50 servings, depending on how much nibbling takes place during the process.

title: pea soup
directions: Bring peas to a boil with salt pork.
Add onion, garlic salt and carrots.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, until peas are completely disintegrated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove salt pork.

title: chicken broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Put in 1/2 of the chicken.
Cover with dry dressing mix.
Add soup and broccoli, then the cheese.
Layer until all ingredients are used, except some of the dressing. Sprinkle it on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp with feta cheese
directions: Clean shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Saute onions in olive oil until soft.
Stir in drained tomatoes, garlic, parsley, oregano, basil, salt, pepper and vermouth.
Cook a little on slow burner.
Set aside.
Stir in clam juice.
Cook 5 minutes.
In another pan, saute shrimp in butter.
Put tomato mixture in shallow casserole.
Pour shrimp over sauce and mix slightly. Crumble Feta and sprinkle over all.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve over linguine with French bread.
Serves 4.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream butter with dark brown sugar.
Sprinkle on and mix into batter the cinnamon, nutmeg and ground cloves.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: joanne's meat loaf(american entree)
directions: Break up meat into bowl.
Set aside.
Make bread crumbs in blender. Mix with milk.
Add Worcestershire sauce, onion, celery salt, garlic salt, pepper and sage. Add this mixture to meat.

title: grandma murrie's perfect apple pie
directions: Slice apples. Combine next 5 ingredients.
Mix.
Fill pie shell with apples and sugar mixture.
Adjust top crust.
Flute edges.
Bake 50 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream ingredients together until fluffy.
Beat 5 minutes. Blend in chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients and mix in alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate butter icing.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix and serve.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 25 servings.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix and serve with fruit.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.
This cake will fall.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until slightly browned.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Beat with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 caramel topping on each cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture on top.
Repeat layers, then freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoon on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute before removing.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers and drain well.
Mix together water, tomato and mushroom soups.
Add soups to hamburger mixture; add garlic.
Mix with cooked spaghetti and bake at 350° until it bubbles through and through.
Serve.
Mix cheese in before baking.
This will freeze very well.
Serves 12.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Top with coconut flakes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Will be golden brown on top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill (other fruit may be added by choice).
Serves 20.

title: braunschweiger ball and bread sticks
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients; shape and cool.
Blend together cream cheese and 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Spread over braunschweiger ball.
Sprinkle with dried parsley and bacon bits. Serve with Bread Sticks.

title: chewys(blonde brownies)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, stirring until dissolved. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, then stir in nuts. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of dish with the pork chops (whatever it takes to cover bottom of dish). Slice the potatoes on top of the pork chops until they are covered.
Also slice onion on top of the potatoes (if desired).
If more pork chops are wanted to feed more people, just add another layer of pork chops and potatoes, etc., according to number of people you are feeding.
Pour small amount of milk into bottom of Pyrex dish to help from sticking.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake in moderate oven until done with lid on Pyrex dish. After they are cooked, drain off all liquid (milk, grease, etc.).
Put grated cheese on top. Most of the time, the heat from the pork chops and potatoes will melt the cheese if top is placed back on.
If not, stick back in oven for just a second.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients. Combine molasses and hot water.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with molasses mixture.
Beat after each addition.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meatballs and spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls and brown in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add meatballs to sauce and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked rotini
directions: In medium skillet, combine beef and onion.
Cook until beef is browned and onion tender.
Drain.
Stir in next 8 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: oil and garlic sauce(all'olio e aglio)
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add garlic and cook until browned.
Stir in water; add parsley and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Pour over pasta and eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a frying pan, bring water to a boil.
Add frozen broccoli. Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain and remove from pan; set aside.
Using same pan, melt 1 stick of butter.
Add Velveeta cheese.
After melted, pour in broccoli.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Melt the other stick of butter.
Then add crushed crackers.
Pour over broccoli; mix.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Sprinkle crushed cereal on bottom of pie plate.
Sprinkle gelatin on milk.
Soften for 5 minutes.
Add sugar.
Boil and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Dream Whip, cottage cheese, yogurt, vanilla and lemon juice.
Combine well and pour into pie plate. Mix Danish Dessert and berries.
Pour over pie.
Chill thoroughly.

title: rub for beef roast
directions: Mix ingredients and rub into roast.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 20 minutes per pound for rare; longer if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine.
Combine butter, hash browns, chicken soup, cheese and sour cream.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread 2 cups cornflakes and 1/2 stick butter (cut into small chunks) over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Marinate flank steak in your favorite marinade overnight.
Cut a pocket in flank steak.
Sprinkle Italian seasoning in pocket. Layer salami, cheese, onion, and salami again in pocket.
Skewer pocket closed.
Broil or barbecue until done.
Remove skewers, slice and serve.

title: special oriental salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; mix until smooth.
Store dressing in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: blue burgers
directions: Blend all ingredients until mixed well.
Form into 1/4 pound patties.
Place on hot grill (charcoal or gas).
Cook until desired temperature, medium or medium well.
Enjoy!! You'll never go back to ordinary cheeseburgers.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with hot water.
Add vanilla.
Batter will be thin. Makes 2 (9-inch) layers or 3 dozen cupcakes, or large 9 x 13-inch cake.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: tuna salad
directions: Chop eggs.
In large bowl combine all ingredients.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Season to your own taste.
Put chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Melt butter and crumble crackers into butter; mix together well.
Spread on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and water; boil until clear.
Add food coloring and Jell-O.
Cool.
Put sliced strawberries in baked pie shell and pour glaze on top.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: grits au gratin
directions: Bake in large casserole for 1 hour at 300°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; spread in oblong Pyrex dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on top and bottom of 4 buns.
Add thinly sliced boiled ham and 1 slice Swiss cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown bread crumbs in skillet with butter. Spread crumbs into baking dish (at least 9-inch square size). Drain asparagus and gently place spears or pieces over the crumbs. Slice the eggs over this, then pour the mushroom soup over the eggs. Sprinkle a few reserved crumbs on top, followed by sprinkling of the grated cheese over the top.
Place in a 350° oven and cook until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: swiss bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in a
little
of
the
warm water.
When well mixed, add the rest
of the water, salt and rye flour and mix well.
Add the white
flour,
a
little
at a time, mixing well after each addition
until
a
fairly stiff dough.
Cover dough and let stand at least 1 1/2 hours or until doubled.
On floured board,
turn dough and knead until smooth.
Divide in 2.
Form each part into a round ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
With a knife, make a cross on top of each loaf.
Cover and let
rise until
double.
Bake
in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Spray 10 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Wash and soak dried beef thoroughly.
Line in bottom of pan.
Skin chicken and discard skin.
Wrap 1 slice of bacon around each piece of chicken and place on top of dried beef.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.
If browning occurs too quickly, cover pan.

title: skillet seafood bisque
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot butter, cook mushrooms, green onions and garlic until vegetables are tender. Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in chicken broth. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer about 5 minutes or until seafood is done. Stir in wine, cream and parsley.
Heat through.
Ladle into bowls and top with dill.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat whites of eggs until stiff and add to other ingredients. Bake in a greased pie plate 25 minutes at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, but not too thin.
Cut peppers and onions in small pieces.
Sprinkle the vegetables with the 1/2 cup salt and use a few lumps of ice.
Let this stand for 3 hours, then drain off this water.
Make a pickling syrup using alum, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour all this in a kettle and stir often, using a wooden spoon.
Let this come to a boil, but do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add frozen strawberries;stir occasionally until thawed, Add crushed pineapple and diced bananas. Pour 1/2 into an 8x8 inch pan.

Chill until firm. Spread 1 cup sour cream over chilled mixture. Pour remaining Jello over top of sour cream ( do not let this part of the jello get chilled, just set aside). Now chill the whole pan until firm. Top with Cool Whip. Cut into squares.

title: chicken creole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: mocha shake special
directions: Mix cocoa and coffee in small bowl of electric mixer.
Blend in hot water.
Add ice cream and cola.
Beat until frothy.
Pour into tall glasses.
Yields 4 glasses.

title: tofu quiche
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and pie crust in bowl.
Add herbs and vegetables.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: herring in sour cream
directions: Drain herring of juices and mix all ingredients.
Place into covered dish and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: aunt susie's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa.
Stir in sugar and milk.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cookies should begin to harden immediately.
Remove cookies from waxed paper when cool.

title: baked buffalo casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.
Preparation Time:
1 1/2 hours.

title: pear or apple squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in and bake for 1 hour at 325° or until done.
Very moist and good.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Saute meat, peppers, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over medium to low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Form into balls somewhat larger than marbles.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze.
Once frozen, store in plastic bags or containers and use number desired.

title: rick's cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; season with salt and oregano. Melt cheese; and stir in tomatoes, bean dip and mushroom soup. Drain grease from browned meat before adding to cheese mixture.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in a big bowl, then add eggs, also, to mixture in
this
bowl.	Melt
oleo
and Crisco.
Add milk to hot mixture.
In a small dish, dissolve cake yeast and warm water. Pour
over
dry
ingredients.
Stir until smooth, then knead until smooth.
Cover
tightly and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: grandmama's surprise(dessert)
directions: Drain pineapple first in colander. Make lemon jello in large pan. Heat all 4 cups water. Cut cream cheese in tiny chunks and melt in jello. Drop in 40 marshmallows and melt.
Cool a bit, then stir in pineapple (drink juice!). Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan and stir in whipped cream.
Let set in refrigerator, then make the red jello as per package. Put in a bowl to get good and cold, but not set.
Pour onto other jello mixture and let set. Cut into squares and eat!

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and Pet milk together and bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, semi-sweets, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour in buttered dish.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium for 5 hours, simmer 3 more hours.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Let first four ingredients set 2 hours.
Drain very well.
Pat with paper towels.
Boil remaining ingredients 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over cucumbers.
Freeze.
Thaw 1/2 hour before serving. Good added to tossed salad.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg, milk and oil and mix just until moistened.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in a pie plate sprayed with cooking oil.

title: summer sausage
directions: First Day:
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon pepper seasoning.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Dice and saute bacon.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and stock.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Add shrimp, okra and rice.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Mix cheese and oleo; add flour and mix well.
Add cereal. Shape in small balls and mash with a fork.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Chop up lettuce and layer on bottom of large dish.
Chop up celery and layer, then onion, then peas and cheese next; all layered on top of the other.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Sprinkle a layer on salad.
Top with Miracle Whip and cover.
Let set before serving.

title: ham and cheese feullitte
directions: Roll out sheet to 1/8-inch thick.
Brush sheet with mustard; top with ham, cheese and top with remaining sheet.
Fold ends together and with a fork, press sides.
Brush egg yolk on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: tomato-cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumber; toss gently and let stand 30 minutes.
Drain cucumber and press dry between paper towels. Combine cucumber, green pepper and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.

title: chinese hash
directions: Brown the meat and add all the ingredients, except the noodles.
Put into a baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Then remove from oven and cover with Chinese noodles.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: lemon cheesecake pie
directions: Combine evaporated milk and pudding mix.
Beat 2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: shannon's special sauce
directions: Use to top your baked potatoes.
Mix all ingredients together and pour onto hot baked potatoes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waldorf coleslaw
directions: Combine first four ingredients and enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.

title: nut kisses
directions: Chop nuts very fine.
Peanuts or pecans are especially good. Beat the egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Fold in the vanilla, salt and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased letter paper or waxed paper.
Bake in a slow oven (275°) for forty to sixty minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: crab stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut top off each cherry tomato; scoop out and discard the pulp, leaving shell intact.
Invert tomato shells on paper towels to drain.
Place cottage cheese in blender or food processor; blend until smooth.
Transfer cottage cheese to a medium bowl; stir in crabmeat and remaining ingredients.
Spoon the mixture evenly into the tomato shells.
Cover; chill well.
Yields 32 appetizers, 11 calories each (16% from fat).

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix the bacon grease, sugar and red wine vinegar and microwave until bubbly.
Toss the spinach, mushrooms, onion, eggs and bacon. Pour the sugar mixture over the spinach; toss and eat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place all ingredients except cracker crumbs in large pot. Cook until meat falls from bones cut up fine.
Grease deep casserole and put in layers of chicken and crumbs.
Top with crumbs.
Pour 3 cups broth chicken was cooked in.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
For an accompanying sauce, mix and heat 1 can mushroom soup with chicken broth.
Serves 8.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain chopped spinach.
Mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Add chopped green onions.
Stir together and chill.
Serve on Hi-Ho crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: beef noodle bake(yield: 6 servings)
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, onions and green bell pepper; mix well.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: oriental broccoli
directions: Boil broccoli about 5 minutes only.
Drain immediately.
While the broccoli is cooking, slice the onion and mushrooms.
Cook the onions and mushrooms together in the margarine and soy sauce for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Put the drained broccoli into a serving dish and pour the onion/mushroom/margarine/soy sauce mixture over top.
Do not stir!
Serve hot.
(It's delicious with steak and rice.)
Serves 4.

title: chocolate marble loaf cake
directions: Heat water and butter; add vanilla and chocolate (melted).
Add sugar and beat to spread consistency.
Spread on loaf cake.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar gradually until well blended.
Add flour, corn syrup, vanilla, margarine, oats and coconut.
Stir well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean). Cool before serving.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, cucumbers, onion, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Separate cooked egg yolks from whites. Dice whites and add to potato mixture.
Sieve yolks and combine with sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar and mustard.
Add to potato mixture and mix carefully.
Chill for several hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scene stealer dip
directions: Cut top off round loaf of bread; hollow out, reserving top. Mix all other ingredients.
Put mixture into hollowed loaf.
Place top of loaf back.
Wrap tightly with heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers or bread cubes.

title: corn spoon
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Spread in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops slightly in small amount of shortening.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine rice, onion soup mix, soup and water.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Place meat on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: In a bowl, combine cooked rice, marshmallows and pineapple. Chill 2 hours.
Beat until stiff the cream; blend in sugar.
Fold into rice mixture; chill.
Garnish with cherries, nuts or toasted coconut.
This may be tinted any color.

title: three day slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion and chop green pepper.
Mix together with the other ingredients.
Better when left 2 or 3 days before serving.
At Christmas it looks pretty to use purple cabbage.

title: mama's jam cake
directions: Pour into 2 lightly greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix
softened cream cheese, sour cream, chilies, onions and olives
together.
Spread on tortillas and roll-up like a jelly roll.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight in a plastic bag. Slice
in
one-inch
slices
before serving.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Let cool, then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: elderberry jelly
directions: Stem and wash berries.
Cover with water and boil 20 minutes. Strain.
To 5 cups of berry juice, add apple juice and Sure-Jell. Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and boil 1/2 minute.
Pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Slice eggplants in half; scoop out some of the inside and chop.
Heat oil in skillet and add eggplant pieces, beef, onion, peppers, garlic, Tabasco and salt.
Saute until eggplants are lightly browned.
Toss in rice and blend all ingredients.
Stuff eggplant halves with filling.
Place stuffed halves skin down in greased baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
You may stuff some green peppers with some of the filling if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon color.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar. Add the Canadian Club and rum.

title: creamy chicken-mushroom soup
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add onion and saute, stirring occasionally, until softened.
Add mushrooms and saute 5 minutes longer.
Remove and reserve 2 tablespoons of mushroom mixture.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables in saucepan and stir quickly to combine.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in water.
Add broth mix and thyme. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour 2 cups of soup in blender and process until smooth.
Transfer to 1-quart bowl and repeat with remaining soup.
Pour soup back into saucepan.
Stir in milk and reserved mushroom mixture and simmer 5 minutes.
Season and garnish with parsley.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake into small pieces.
Put some into bottom of large bowl or punch bowl.
Next, put 1/2 of crushed pineapple on top, then half of vanilla pudding.
Keep alternating until all used up. Then put pie filling on top of cake mixture at end.
Finally, top with whipped topping.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
It's better if made the night before so all the goodies have time to soak into the cake.

title: apple pie & crust
directions: Cut in flour, salt and shortening. Add water and mix by hand. Roll out crust.

title: finger jell-o
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold tap water.
Add Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate until jelled before putting on second layer, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Make sure liquid is cool enough not to melt jelled layer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat well. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Add flour and soda. Mix well. Roll in small balls. Press down with fork dipped in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chili hominy bake
directions: Crumble beef and saute with onions until meat is slightly browned.
Stir in chili, chili powder, chicken soup, hominy and olives.
Spread in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Spread on top of jello.

title: sausage macaroni broccoli casserole
directions: Cook all vegetables and macaroni as directed.
When done, combine all and mix with sausage that has been microwaved 2 minutes.
Top with croutons.
Can be reheated, when ready to serve, in the microwave.
A meal all in one.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Place half of broccoli in bottom of baking dish.
Melt cheese and margarine.
Pour half melted cheese over broccoli.
Top with half mixture of crackers.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: viennese-style fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Spread with mustard.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Arrange fish on greased rack in baking dish.
Combine ham, sour cream, flour, pickle and onion.
Spread on top of fish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over fish.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes more or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 6 servings.
Per serving:
190 calories, 7 grams fat, 77 milligrams cholesterol.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix together, then add 2 cups crab meat.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole and bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add marshmallows, stirring until almost melted.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Add pineapple, cold water, bananas and pecans to gelatin; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until set. Combine reserved juice, egg, flour and sugar in saucepan; mix well.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter and cream cheese until melted.
Chill completely.
Prepare whipped topping using package directions.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over gelatin.
Chill for several hours.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream in large bowl the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Thoroughly mix the remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light tan.
Don't overbake.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: Sauce:
Cook ground beef until done.
Drain off grease.
Add Italian spices, salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce to ground beef. Mix well.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce mix. Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne noodles.
Top with some sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly browned and bubbling. Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Cut fillets in serving pieces; place in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour, dry mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over fillets.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm crumbs and parsley.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or 1/2 cup flaked coconut.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack, then chill.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in butter until vegetables are tender. Add flour and curry powder. Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in half and half. Cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice, remaining seasoning and shrimp to sauce.
Heat thoroughly. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in Saran Wrap in small bowl and chill until firm.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Keeps well for several days.

title: casserole chop suey
directions: Cook meat until lightly browned.
Mix everything together. Bake, uncovered, at 350°, until rice is done (about 1 1/2 hours), stirring after one hour.
When done, stir everything, then cover with chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat until bubbly.
Add balance of flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly and let rise until double. Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
(It's easier if the dough is divided in half.)
Spread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon to suit taste.
Raisins may be added also.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut.
Raise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan (hard to spread).
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread onto crust.
Chill 15 minutes.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until thick.
Pour on. Garnish with pecans (optional).
One hour before serving, spread with more Cool Whip.
Serves 15.

title: swiss eggs
directions: Slightly cook sausage or bacon; put in bottom of pan.
Add butter and cheese slices.
Break eggs over cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour cream over eggs.
Sprinkle with a little grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until eggs are set.

title: pasta foozle
directions: In medium saucepan, combine paste and sauce.
Add 3 paste cans of water and 1 sauce can of water.
Mix all together and cook until it thickens (about 1 hour).
Add one can of white beans and simmer on low heat.
In another pot, cook 1 pound of ditalini according to package directions.
Drain and add to sauce.

title: tuna pate
directions: Put all in bowl except mayonnaise.
Blend with electric mixer until smooth.
Scoop out tuna mixture; put in serving dish and spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: party mix
directions: First you put in some nuts.
Next one cup of bread sticks. Shake them up.
Then put in your pretzels and Cherreos.
Last you put in checks and then you shake them up for about 2 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and use about 1/3 to 1/2 cup of mix for each cup of hot chocolate.
Fill with boiling hot water.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove sauce from heat when it begins to bubble.
Add cheese and other ingredients at this time.
Stir until smooth.
Makes 2 cups.

title: daddy's biscuits
directions: In large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
Melt margarine, add to dry mixture; add milk.
Mix by hand with a pastry cutter.
Flour cutting board, place dough on board.
Mold with hands to about 1 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Place in shallow baking pan, sides touching.
Bake at 450° until light brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O dry into Cool Whip.

title: party mix
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients in pan; heat on stove until butter melts.
Put remaining ingredients in large pan with cover.
Pour sauce over it and mix well.
Cook 1 hour at 225° with cover, then remove cover and cook 1 more hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onions, carrots and celery and saute until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk and make smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese. Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Very good and a nice soup to serve to a ladies luncheon.

title: philadelphia cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and cheese until it is like whipped cream.
Add the sugar gradually, never losing the whipped cream consistency.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Add egg yolk and beat in well.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add in three additions, mixing after each.
Chill dough 10 minutes. Pack in cookie press. Make in desired shape.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and 1/2 cup whipping cream to make paste.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
Fill crust with sliced fresh peaches.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for about 1 hour or until brown (apples can be used also).

title: basket dessert
directions: Crumble in bowl the Shredded Wheat.
Stir in brown sugar and 1/4 cup sugar.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Toss to coat. Spray 12 muffin cups with Pam.
Press mixture into cups.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool in cups; carefully remove with knife.

title: apple bavarian torte
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until completely blended.
Pour the mixture into the prepared crust.
Prepare the topping.

title: mom's date nut pudding
directions: Boil 5 minutes sugar, water and butter.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Drop 2nd mixture into first in a large casserole. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes; stir and then bake 5 to 15 minutes.
Chill.
Serve cold with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix vanilla pudding as instructions on the box. Add sour cream. Pinch cake in pieces and put in a large bowl.
Pour pudding and sour cream mix over the cake. Spoon cherry pie filling over the top and refrigerate.
(Children would love making this recipe.)

title: teriyaki chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow 2-quart microwave-safe dish or 10-inch pie plate with meaty portions of chicken toward outer edge of dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours, turning chicken over once.
Drain and discard marinade.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Cook on High power 8 to 10 minutes, rotating dish once. Let stand 3 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake(senior citizen delight)
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, brown sugar and spices in small bowl and beat until sugar is well mixed.
Add to cake in larger bowl with rest of ingredients and beat 3 minutes at medium speed of hand mixer.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven for
to
minutes,
or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Turn
out
on rack and cool.
Serve plain or with a confectioners sugar glaze.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with half the sugar and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and let it sit.
Put butter in pan and place in the oven on low to melt.
Unroll 1 can of Pillsbury crescent rolls.
Roll crescents until completely flat.
Lay over in the pan.
Pour the mixture in.
Take the second can of crescents out and flatten.
Cut into strips and place over the mixture.
Take stick of butter and cut fine slices over the strips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.
Serve with ice cream.

title: ham, chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Place in oblong casserole; mix stuffing as directed on box but do not use liquid. Sprinkle on top; bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: herb breast of dove
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and dry doves.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Let them stand about 15 minutes.
Pour most over doves.
Place in oven about 1 hour. About 10 minutes before removing from oven, pour remaining sauce over doves.

title: peanut butter cookies by aunt bessie barlowe
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar with ingredients to make stiff batter.
Roll in small balls and press 2 ways with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° until cookies are browned around the edges.

title: mexicali meat pie
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, break into large pieces and chill 1/3 cup drippings until firm.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in corn, green peppers, onion, cornmeal, oregano, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and tomato sauce.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Put in microwave dish for 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir every 1 to 2 minutes until thick. When thick, cool and use.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, jello and boiling water on double boiler.
Cook until thickened, then let cool.
Cook 2 pie shells. Place strawberries in bottom of pie shells.
Pour strawberry mix over top and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry topped cheesecake
directions: Measure out 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, stir together remaining dry cake mix, 1 egg and Crisco oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture into bottom and 3/4 of the way up sides of a greased 13 x 9 pan.
In same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Add 3 eggs and rest of cake mix. Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, gradually add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crumb crust. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, until center is firm.
Cool.
Spoon cherries over cake and chill 1 hour.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
On a bed of shredded lettuce, spread mixture.
Top with cheese and 1 large bag Fritos (crushed).

title: orange roughy
directions: Melt butter and mix with lemon juice.
Pour over fillets in baking dish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Great served with salad and breadsticks.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Chill jello with pineapple until partly thickened.
Add blueberry filling.
Just before serving, cover with bananas and Cool Whip.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups water; bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in coffee, using a wire whip.
Cool; add vodka and vanilla bean.
Pour into a large jar.
Cover; let stand at least 3 weeks.
Remove vanilla bean and enjoy.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Combine salt, celery salt, garlic salt, paprika and nutmeg; mixing well.
Dip chicken in milk, roll in corn flake crumbs, coating well.

title: roast beef & yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put meat in oven fat side up, coating with oil.
Cook for about 1 1/4 hours.
Baste frequently.

title: trackside pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat until done, drain.
Add soup and tomato sauce, mix well.
Crush chips, put layer of chips, meat mixture and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mel's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato sauce.
Form into 1 large or 2 small loaves in pan.
Baste with tomato sauce every 15 minutes.
Cook for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: abbie's olives and bacon treats
directions: Quarter biscuit dough.
Place an olive in.
Wrap bacon around the biscuit dough.
Hold it in place until cooked with toothpick. Cook until dough is brown and bacon is cooked.

title: white chili
directions: Place chicken in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to simmer.
Cook until just tender.
About 15 minutes. Remove from pan, drain and cool.
Remove skin; cut chicken into cubes.
Using same pan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add onions and saute until translucent.
Stir in garlic, then chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne pepper; saute for 2 minutes. Add undrained beans and stock then bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add chicken and cheese to chili.
Stir until cheese melts. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle into bowls; garnish with sour cream.

title: zesty sausage squares
directions: Mix biscuit mix with milk and 2 tbsp.

mayonnaise. Spread on well greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Saute meat and onions, drain. Spread meat onto biscuit mixture. Beat together, egg and remaining 2 tbsp. mayonnaise, cheese and peppers. Spread mixture on top of meat layer. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: raisin spice oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices in bowl. Add shortening, sugars, egg and milk. Beat until smooth. Fold in raisins and oats. Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apricot nuggets
directions: Chop apricots and pecans in food processor or chopper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with fork or knead.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 6 dozen nuggets.

title: fred's pinto beans
directions: Fill gallon pot with water.
Cook on medium heat and boil steady for four hours.
You can put four medium peeled onions in at start if you want to.
Eat with green onions and light bread or corn bread.

title: fabulous french onion
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for 5 minutes.

title: spring vegetable macaroni salad
directions: Mix yogurt, mustard, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Chill.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point, add lime jello and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese, stir in pimiento, and add to jello mixture and blend.
Fold in whipped cream, celery and nuts.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.

title: coal miner's spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.
Cook and stir garlic and bacon in oil until bacon is crisp.
Drain.
Mix eggs, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese, parsley and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.

title: betty's cheese dip
