directions: Put all ingredients in microwave-safe container.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.
Stir.
Serve hot with chips, nachos or raw vegetables.

title: dump cake
directions: First Layer:
1 1/2 cups chopped pecans.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with snack crackers or chips.
Good recipe for parties.

title: party punch
directions: Ingredients should be combined and divided into batches, depending on the size of punch bowl. Strawberry slices and ginger ale are added just before serving over ice cubes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Grease pan.
Pour whole can of pineapple and juice in bottom, then cherry filling.
Sprinkle white cake mix and slightly press down.
Cut up oleo on top and add nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Mix well and cook in oven for 25 minutes at 300°.

title: italian mushrooms
directions: Saute chopped garlic.
Add margarine, tomato paste and mushrooms, including liquid.
Simmer about 1 hour (do not add salt).

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
In a medium bowl, sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
In a small bowl, combine milk and lemon juice.
Add flour and milk/lemon juice mixture to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in dates and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions, or chop finely.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain and repeat.
Drain dry. Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook 15 minutes and pack in hot sterilized jars; seal.
Process in water for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries and jello until jello is dissolved (do not add water).
Set aside to cool.
Beat pudding and milk until set. Stir in sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Pour 1/3 of pudding mixture over wafers.
Add 1/2 of strawberries.
Repeat, ending with pudding mixture.

title: grilled chicken sandwiches
directions: Pound breast halves.
Combine soy sauce and next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken and let stand 30 minutes.
Grill over hot coals 30 minutes, turning and basting with marinade every 5 minutes. Add cheese slices to chicken about 5 minutes before done.
Serve with lettuce and tomato on rolls.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put Stove Top stuffing to cover on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Parboil celery 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Form into patties; roll in remaining bread crumbs.
Fry in shortening until golden brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: 5 pounds of fudge
directions: Put in large pan the sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to boil and time it, letting it boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter, chocolate bits, Marshmallow Fluff and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all well (excluding crumbs and cheese).
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: peggy's taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
In separate bowl, cut up fresh vegetables.
Just before serving, add meat, beans, cheese and salad dressing.
Mix thoroughly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda.
Add buttermilk and eggs, then melted butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
This makes 2 thin pies in 9-inch pans.
Bake approximately 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Pour into pans lined with your favorite crust.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar, molasses and egg to oil.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill several hours.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef. Combine with remaining ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Prepare cookie mix according to directions on package or make your own sugar cookie dough.
Roll dough with your hands into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Insert wooden stick halfway into each ball of dough.
Dip bottom of glass into sugar and flatten cookies.
Decorate cookies with raisins and mixed fruit or decorate with sprinkles.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Salt chicken and place in a baking dish.
Make sure that chicken covers bottom of dish.
Combine rest of ingredients, adding wine last.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: marshmallow and pineapple delight
directions: Mix and let stand overnight to soak up the juices.
Serve in parfait glasses with graham cracker crumbs.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, white sugar, eggs and 1 stick of margarine and place in greased baking dish.
Blend brown sugar, 1/3 stick margarine and flour until crumbly.
Sprinkle on mixture and bake at 350° for thirty minutes.

title: bananas baked in foil
directions: You will need 4 pieces of aluminum foil.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: You will need 1 Brown-in-Bag.

title: overnight macaroons (no coconut)
directions: Combine oatmeal, sugar and oil.
Let stand until oil absorbs oatmeal and sugar (overnight).
Mix beaten egg, salt and vanilla in mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle chips on top; allow to stand several minutes.
Spread melted chips to frost.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: crisp cereal pie crust
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir in butter. Spray a 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Press pie crust mixture on bottom and sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 1 crust.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and milk in large pot with cover.
Let mixture heat until butter is melted; do not boil.
Remove from heat; let stand until cool.
Sift together flour and salt. Dissolve yeast with very lukewarm water.
Add to cooled mixture the yeast, then add flour, stirring well and whip well for about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rise for 2 hours, or until doubled.
Use melted for rolls, when mixture has been kneaded well and cut out. Flap over each roll.
Fold in half and place on greased baking pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue bean salad
directions: Combine vegetables and toss lightly.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.
Drain.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar, vanilla, and butter.
Add to 1 cup scalded milk.
Stir well.
Pour into pie crust.
Place on cookie sheet in 375° preheated oven.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Yields on 9 inch pie.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the sugar, Karo and oleo; mix into popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Put on foil; break up into pieces.

title: "numete" sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, lightly fork-mash the Numete.
Mix in lightly the mayonnaise and relish.
Try a taste and add more mayo or relish if needed.
Spoon mixture onto a slice of bread and spread.
You may add whatever else you like.
Suggestions:
onion, tomato, cheese and lettuce, then top with other slice of bread for a delicious sandwich.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and toss with vegetables.

title: sugarless fruit bars
directions: In medium saucepan, cook dates, prunes, and raisins in water for 3-4 minutes.
Cool this mixture and then add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, and cinnamon.
Add this and the vanilla to the fruit/egg mixture, blending well.
Spread in a greased 10 x 13 baking dish.
You may use Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or at 325° if glass dish is used.
Cut into preferred size bars when partially cooled.
Makes 16 (1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: strawberry sherbet(without milk)
directions: Mash or puree berries.
Make syrup of sugar and water.
Add gelatin that has been soaked in cold water.
Chill.
Add berries and juice of 1 lemon; freeze.
If berries are very acid, increase sugar.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Crumble sausage into 2-quart casserole. Stir in onion and green pepper. Microwave on Medium-high until sausage loses pink color, 7 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Drain off excess fat. Toss with bouquet sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave on Medium-high until cabbage is tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place pared, sliced apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon; add water.
Cream together sugar, flour and butter. Spread this mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and place in baking dish.
Add layer of chopped onions.
Add layer of drained green beans.
Place layer of Tater Tots on top.
Mix soup and can of milk by heating together and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown and crusty.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour in one 9-inch casserole.

title: light trifle(a summertime treat)
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Stir in 3 cups of whipped topping.
Place half the cake cubes in a large serving bowl.
Top with half the fruit.
Spread pudding mixture over fruit.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Put grated cheese and mushroom soup over vegetables and onions.
Bake in microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hanky panky
directions: Spread on slices of rye bread (2 loaves).
Place slices on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in airtight bag and store in freezer until needed.
To serve, bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rosy-lemon pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in heavy frying pan over medium heat, turning as needed to brown evenly; drain off excess drippings.
Sprinkle chops with salt.
Place 2 lemon slices on each chop.
Mix catsup and honey; pour over chops.
Cover; cook slowly until chops are fork-tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chops from sauce; set aside to keep warm.
Blend water and cornstarch; stir into pan drippings. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Serve with chops or rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add alternately to creamed mixture with applesauce.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Turn batter into greased and lightly floured muffin pans, fill 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-sauced pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil. Drain and set aside.
Shred 2 teaspoons orange peel. Squeeze 1 cup orange juice (set aside 1/2 cup).
Add 1/2 cup juice to skillet with chops.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: bread and butter cucumbers
directions: In a 4-quart enamel or stainless steel pan over high heat, heat sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed to boiling, stirring often.
Add cucumbers and onion; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in covered glass container in fridge.
Use within 1 month.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: italian goulash
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add ground beef and brown, then drain.
Add tomatoes, Spanish rice and parsley flakes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: crustless brownie pie(very easy; can freeze)
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: sweet-sour hot dogs
directions: Heat mustard and jelly.
Pour in hot dogs.
Stir and refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot in the sauce.

title: crab cakes with aged cheddar
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a bowl, combine crab, mustard, cayenne, green onion, egg and mayonnaise. Stir to mix well.
Divide mixture into 8 equal portions. Shape each into a ball, then flatten into a 1/2-inch thick patty. Set aside.

title: great icing
directions: Beat all ingredients until texture is thick.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Make Italian dressing per instructions on package.
Add all ingredients; chill.

title: aunt betty's beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 250° for 3-4 hours.
Should be dark when done.
Serves 10.

title: chow-chow
directions: Mix vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Add sugar and spices to vinegar (20 minutes).
Add all the other ingredients and simmer.

title: potato salad
directions: Toss all the ingredients together lightly and chill well before serving.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower, but not until tender. Put soup in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole. Add half of cheese and half of onion rings. Add broccoli and cauliflower. Add rest of cheese, margarine and onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownies for diabetics
directions: Cream oleo and sweetener.
Add melted chocolate, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, milk and butter together.
Bring to a boil. Let boil for 5 minutes.
Remove pan from heat; add oatmeal, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Spoon out on wax paper and let cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water until dissolved; let cool.
Add pineapple, orange juice and 1 can water.
Add bananas and freeze.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Drop cookies in milk, one at a time, and take right out. Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with cookies.
Cover cookies with Cool Whip.
Repeat until completed.

title: jessie cakes
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan; turn off heat.
Add brown sugar and stir well, but do not cook.
Remove from heat; add eggs and mix.
Add flour, baking powder and nuts; mix well.
Spread mixture into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; then cut into squares.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Bring cranberries, sugar and lemon juice to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 25 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add orange marmalade, lemon rind and Amaretto.
Put on top of cream cheese and serve with crackers (Wheat Thins).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Chill.
When ready to serve, hollow out a round loaf of pumpernickel or rye bread.
Cut the hollowed out part into serving pieces, and place the dip into hollowed out loaf to serve. Place serving pieces around the loaf.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray Pam on muffin tins (makes 12 or so).
Combine egg, applesauce, milk, oil, sugar and raisins in mixing bowl.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon until well blended.
Do not beat.
Spoon into greased muffin tin sprayed with Pam.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
You may want to put a sprinkle of streusel on top before baking.

title: pecan fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, including pecans, in a large heavy pan. Bring to 240° on candy thermometer (which must be used for satisfactory results).
Use medium heat.
When 240° temperature is reached, set off stove and cool to warm, 25 minutes or so.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until thick.
Pour into large buttered cake pan.
Cut in pieces when set.

title: turkey chili
directions: Fry turkey until no longer pink and drain off fat and water. In large pot, stir in turkey, undrained tomatoes, kidney beans (drained), tomato sauce, onion, chili powder, parsley, basil, oregano, pepper, cinnamon, garlic, red pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each egg is added.
Combine all together and pour in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked deep pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together into a crock-pot and heat until warm.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or chips of your own choice.
Recipe may be doubled for full crock-pot.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over pretzels, stirring to coat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix the jello, hot water and cold water; let set until firm. Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: cheddar spinach squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Press crescent roll dough into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat and seal any perforation in dough.
In medium bowl, combine cheese, flour, then add eggs, half and half, salt, pepper, nutmeg and garlic powder.
Then add spinach.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until well set.
Cut into squares. Serve warm.
Makes approximately 24 to 36 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash
sweet
potatoes
and
let
set overnight or until cold. Add
butter, sugar, milk and salt.	Press around marshmallows
and roll in flakes and coconut mixture.
Cook at 300° until hot and lightly browned.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt; pour over melted butter.
Pour a can of fruit (any fruit) with liquid on top of dough.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Dough will come to the top.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine soups, butter, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all and form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind onions and green peppers.
Cut up tomatoes.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.

title: chocolate chips and peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use electric mixer and beat eggs, dark corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in peanuts.
Sprinkle pie shell with chocolate chips.
Pour filling over chips.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking 30 to 35 minutes or when toothpick comes out of center dry.
Cool.
Cover with plastic and put in refrigerator overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese; beat.
Add pineapple, not drained and let congeal.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; rinse with cold water.
Add bell pepper, onion and carrots.
Mix mayonnaise, Eagle Brand milk, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over macaroni.
Stir in cubed cheese.
Chill for 4 to 12 hours before serving.

title: chicken breast with sour cream gravy
directions: In large glass baking dish layer the chipped beef.
Wrap chicken breasts with bacon strips and place on chipped beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream together with about 2 ounces of water. Pour this mixture over the chicken and cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: tuna noodle casserole(health conscious)
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic.
Combine onion and garlic with tuna, green pepper, carrots, parsley and paprika; set aside.
In a small bowl, blend together sour cream, cottage cheese and yogurt.
Add to tuna mixture, along with noodles.
Pour into casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until top is lightly browned.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Spray a 3 or 4-quart baking dish with Pam.
Spread apple pie filling on bottom.
Drain and chop the sweet potatoes and layer over apples.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Top with bits of margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour and soda into mixing bowl.
Blend in shortening, adding buttermilk gradually until smooth.
Toss on floured surface.
Roll out into 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut and place on greased shallow pan.
Bake at 400°.

title: easy, cheesy green bean pasta
directions: Drain green beans reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine green beans and reserved liquid with remaining ingredients; heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, peppers and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Mix remaining ingredients together with sauteed vegetables.
Place in glass baking dish and bake in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple custard pie
directions: Combine sweet milk, unsweetened applesauce, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until knife point near center comes out clean.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and add remaining ingredients. Mix together and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Blanch celery for approximately 4 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Place in casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crunch top apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in bottom of pie crust.
Put on top lattice crust.
Then put on Crunch Topping.

title: spinach-artichoke salad
directions: Tear spinach and lettuce in bite sized pieces; slice onions and mushrooms.
Combine.
Toss with oil and vinegar.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add artichoke hearts and croutons.
Yields 8 generous servings.
(My favorite for 8-at-8 dinners.)

title: cheese sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together and heat in saucepan.
Pour over cooked vegetables, such as cauliflower or broccoli.

title: chicken in sour cream with dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; rub with soya sauce, then dust well with flour.
Add 2 tablespoons cooking oil in skillet and fry chicken until brown.
Lay in deep casserole with cover.
Add lima beans and sour cream over chicken; cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Add dumplings by spoonfuls.
Cover tightly again and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: shrimp-cream cheese spread
directions: Mix and spread on Sociables crackers.
To make dip, add sour cream (to taste).

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Combine pretzels, butter and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray (Pam).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Heat a little sausage in a baking pan and when smoking hot, pour in the batter.
Put
the sausages in the batter and bake in hot oven at 450° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Serve at once.

title: norman's honeyed chicken breasts
directions: Make sauce mixing all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken skin side up in single layer in baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, basting at 15 minute intervals.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Saute onion, green pepper, celery and chilies in sausage.
Place bread cubes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom chicken(cook in crock-pot)
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towel.
Mix soup and broth until well blended.
Place chicken in crock-pot and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours (high 4 to 5 hours).
Chicken will be very tender and fall off the bones.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine eagle brand milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding into 2 1/2 quart glass serving bowl. Top with one third each of the wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Keep chilled.

title: horseradish sour cream beans
directions: Marinate beans in mixture overnight.
Drain well and mix with the following dressing:

title: dark and spicy pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes more.

title: oven-fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine water and egg.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture, then dredge in cornmeal.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn once.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix together; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat cast-iron corn stick pan in oven while preparing batter.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Use glass container.
Cook brown sugar, corn syrup and whipping cream on High for 13 minutes, then add margarine and pecans.
Beat by hand until loses its gloss.
Then drop by teaspoon on foil.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together thoroughly Parmesan cheese, corn flakes, garlic salt, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Dredge chicken in melted butter, then coat thoroughly with Parmesan cheese and corn flake mixture.
Put in oblong casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "more"
directions: Saute chopped meat in skillet. Boil water for noodles, add noodles but only cook for 5 minutes.
Grate cheese.
Drain meat when done.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan or Corning Ware.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes and serve.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with garlic powder.
Marinate overnight in liquid smoke plus a small amount of water.
The next morning pour off the liquid.
Cover the pan and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Pour barbecue sauce over the brisket and cook uncovered for 30 minutes. Cool and refrigerate before slicing or serve right away.
Cut the brisket on a slant.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter over low heat. Stir constantly.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press 1/2 of mixture in 8-inch square greased pan.
Chill in freezer.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one bowl.
Beat for 20 minutes, stirring now and then.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Put in cold oven and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or test with toothpick for doneness.
You can sprinkle 10x sugar on top if desired.

title: my corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 3-quart casserole dish.
In a large bowl, combine corn and carrots.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into the prepared casserole.
Set dish in a baking pan and add enough boiling water to come halfway up the side.
Bake the pudding about 1 hour, until custard is set, but still jiggly in center (a knife inserted at the side of the pudding should come out clean).
Remove dish from water and cool at least 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon basil pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt in cooking water.
Drain and return pasta to pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice pickles.
Let stand in salt water overnight; drain. Heat in 1 pint vinegar and 1 pint water until they turn yellow. Drain.
Pack in jars.
Boil last 4 ingredients for 4 minutes, then pour over the pickles in jar and seal.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Drain 1 1/2 cups juice.
Bring juice to boil.
Add jello that has been prepared with 2 cups water.
Drain pineapple and mash bananas.
Add fruit to jello.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix jello, pineapple, sugar and eggs together.
Cook until thick.
Cool, then add chilled whipped cream.
Pour into cool pie shell.
Set in icebox and chill.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Put flour into a flat dish and mix in salt and pepper. Dip each piece of chicken into buttermilk, then dredge in flour.
Set aside.
Put lard and butter into a large skillet.
Heat until hot. Very quickly, put in pieces of chicken.
Brown on both sides, then reduce heat and cover with a tight lid.
Fry about 20 minutes or until tender.

title: screwdriver smooth
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until ice is crushed and blended into a frothy, creamy blend.
Serve immediately.
May be garnished with orange slices.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all but last ingredient until smooth with mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a ball.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken pieces, boned side up, on cutting board. Working from center out, pound chicken lightly with wooden mallet to make cutlets about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place a ham slice and a cheese stick on each cutlet.
Tuck in sides of each and roll up as for jelly roll, pressing to seal well.
Skewer or tie securely.
Coat rolls with the 1/4 cup of flour; brown in the butter or margarine.
Remove chicken to a 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Mix equal parts of sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add seasonings to taste.
If sauce is too thick, add canned cream.
Boil potatoes. Cool, peel and slice into thin rounds.
Mix sauce into potatoes to coat evenly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat potatoes; drain juice.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into well buttered baking dish.

title: sac-a-lait sauce piquant
directions: Heat oil in heavy 5-quart Dutch oven; add flour.
Make a roux to a deep caramel color, careful not to burn.
Add all chopped ingredients, one at a time.
Stir well.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Place fish on cutting board and sprinkle liberally on both sides with Cajun seasoning.
Place fish in lightly oiled baking dish.
Cover fish with sauce piquant.
(Reserve any leftover sauce for side dish.) Cover casserole dish with foil and bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon pecan freezer cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and extract.
Combine dry ingredients; add gradually to butter-sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Separate the dough into 4 equal portions.
Shape each portion into a log; wrap in wax paper.
Put logs in freezer.
When ready to bake, cut log into 3/8-inch slices and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown around the edges.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and place in a greased baking dish. Pour glaze over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: dill cream soup
directions: When potatoes are almost cooked, add sour cream (can be thinned with milk), mixed with flour.
When the soup comes to a boil, add chopped dill.
Raw eggs may be dropped into the soup after it is thickened and cooked over a slow fire or it may be served with hard-boiled eggs.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons vinegar for added flavor.

title: italian salad
directions: I use food
processor;	if not, cut in pieces.	Put all ingredients and stir on the following:

title: williamsburg orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round pans.

Beat all ingredients constantly 30 seconds on low speed, then 3 minutes on high speed. Pour into pan(s) and bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (oblong 45 to 50 minutes, layer 30 to 35 minutes). Cool and frost.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together until crumbly like pie crust.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot burgundy and cider
directions: Heat the cider, lemon juice, cinnamon sticks, cloves and sugar in a large pot.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Heat to a boil; remove from the heat.
Add the wine and place the mixture in a crock-pot to keep it warm during the serving period.
Yields 1 1/4 gallons.

title: pickled cucumbers
directions: Put vinegar, sugar and spices together and cook until it boils.
Cut up cucumbers, green pepper and onion.
Place vegetables in large jar and pour liquid over.
Store in refrigerator.
You can also use cauliflower and broccoli.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg, celery and onion in melted butter or margarine.
Add other ingredients and simmer slowly, about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk.
Stir. Add scalding milk. Stir.
Pour into pie shells and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 pies.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and sugar in bowl.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush all of cookies in blender.
Save some cookies for top. Mix butter and rest of cookies together and spread on bottom of cake pan.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and milk together.
Pour on top of crust and chill 1 hour.
Make pudding for pie filling and spread on top of cake mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cookies on top. Chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini 5 minutes in small amount of water; drain. Cook onion in 1/2 stick butter. Add tomatoes; cook until thick. Add cheese, salt, pepper and sugar. Put crackers in oven with 1/2 stick butter; stir until well coated. Cover bottom of baking dish with zucchini, then alternate with tomato mixture and crackers. Top with crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: boneless skinless chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in glass baking dish.
Put 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon sour cream on top of each breast.
Pour soup over breasts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle fried onions over top.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Mix these in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: popcorn balls("kids cooking")
directions: Younger children will need help with microwave.

title: 10x sugar cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend 3 sticks margarine; add 1 box 10x sugar.
Add 2 cups of flour and 6 eggs (one at a time).
Add vanilla; turn in well-greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open oven.

title: frozen fruit loaf
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in pineapple.
Stir in 7-Up. Sprinkle sugar over peaches and grapes and stir into mixture.
Pour into 2-quart freezable dish and freeze until partially thickened. Whip cream until stiff.
Fold in marshmallows.
Fold cream mixture into fruit mixture and freeze until solid.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then pour over oyster crackers and stir to coat.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Cut top of French bread about 1/4-inch from side and bottom.
Cut bread top into squares for dipping.
Use bottom as bowl.
Put filling in bread bowl.

title: pina colada cake(coconut)
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (greased and floured).
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Mix milk, cream of coconut and 1 package fresh coconut.
Pour mixture over cake and into holes.
Let set about 5 minutes.
Mix remaining coconut and Cool Whip.
Spoon on cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter.
Combine avocados and lemon juice and spread over dip.
Then combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning and spread over avocados.
Then put remaining ingredients on top.
Chill.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Shape into balls using rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top each with a kiss and press down so cookie cracks on edges.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer until golden brown.

title: shepard pie
directions: Put one layer of potatoes, one layer of meat, one layer of cheese, one layer of vegetables and one layer of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add onion, milk and egg. Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil (360°).
Fry until golden brown.

title: beef stroganoff meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Shape mixture into a 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Transfer meat loaf to a serving platter and keep warm. Combine bouillon granules, flour and water in a small saucepan. Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Combine sour cream, green onions and white pepper; add to bouillon mixture, stirring well.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly (do not boil).
Spoon evenly over meat loaf.
Serve warm.
Yield:
6 servings.
Contains 196 calories per serving and 8.2 g fat.

title: english trifle
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of pretty glass bowl.
Sprinkle with sherry.
Spread jam over cake.
Drain fruit; arrange over jam. Prepare pudding.
Flavor with rum.
Pour over fruit.
Sprinkle with coconut.
When pudding is set, add layer of whipped cream. Add garnish with a pretty fruit like raspberries.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Cut chicken into 12 strips.
Set aside.
In saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chiles, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat. Dip each tortilla in tomato mixture to soften.
Place 1 piece of chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend sour cream into remaining sauce mixture and pour over burritos. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: dave's cabbage rolls
directions: Boil head of cabbage until soft.
Separate leaves.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with French salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Top with hard-boiled eggs.
Serve on lettuce.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in hot iron skillet that has the oil in it.
Spoon some of the oil as it rises over the top of meal mixture.
Bake until golden brown at 425°.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Boil sugar and milk 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Stir well. Cool awhile and drop on greased cookie sheet.

title: party casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in buttered casserole; cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove foil and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to melt cheese.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in Crisco until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer.

title: lydia and joyce's meat loaf
directions: Chop green pepper and onion fine.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
If mixture is too moist, add cracker crumbs.
If too dry, add milk or water.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and place in bottom of baking dish.
Place layer of pizza sauce over meat.
Next, cover sauce with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Combine Bisquick and milk.
Pour over cheese. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Add any other of your favorite pizza toppings if desired.

title: salmon filet, marinated in red wine
directions: Place salmon filet in marinating dish and spread onion, carrot and juniper berries around fish.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Add wine; cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours. Brush cooking surface with
oil.
Heat
oven
Remove fish from marinade and place, skin side down, on oven grill or in shallow pan.
Brush
fish lightly with melted butter.
Bake for
about 10 minutes,
or
until
fish
flakes
when
tested. Remove fish and cooking
surface from oven, and carefully peel flesh away from skin.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Melt ingredients together and then pour in glass dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: 7-layer heartburn dip
directions: Mix beans and taco sauce together.
Spread on large glass dish.
Spread sour cream on top of beans.
Spread jalapeno peppers on next.
Spread sliced or chopped olives next.
Spread scallions or onions next.
Spread chopped tomatoes next.
Spread cheese (grated or chopped) on top! It is a little runny at first. It will thicken as it cools.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serve with corn chips to dip into this mess!!

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: In a large bowl, pour milk over rolled oats.
Add shortening, molasses and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water; add to cooled oat mixture.
Stir in flour to make a stiff dough.
On floured board, knead dough until smooth and satiny, adding flour as needed.
Place dough in large bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Turn dough onto lightly oiled surface.
Divide in half.
Shape each half into a loaf.

title: spicy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: marinated tomato salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, olives, onion and dressing.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.
To serve, line plates with lettuce.
Top with marinated mixture and sliced avocado.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, soften yeast in warm water.
Add granulated sugar, oil, eggs, salt and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat with an electric mixer on high for 3 minutes.
Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can with a spoon.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead in as much of the remaining flour as you can to make a moderately soft dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down dough and divide in half.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 of the dough into an 18 x 11-inch rectangle. Spread dough with half of the butter.
Sprinkle half of the brown sugar and cinnamon over butter.
Roll up from one of the short sides and pinch edges to seal.
Slice into 8 pieces.
Place rolls, cut side down, in a greased 13 x 9-inch dish or a 12-inch pizza pan.
Repeat with remaining dough, sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
It makes 16 rolls.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with crunched Ramen noodles.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add milk and beaten egg; mix well.
Sift the flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt together and add raisins about halfway in batter when mixing together.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick on floured board. Cut with cookie cutter any size.
Bake in hot oven 12 minutes.
When cool, ice with Cocoa Icing.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: fresh apple crunch cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add apples, nuts, vanilla and brandy.
Mix all together.
Batter will be stiff like a cookie dough.
Pour in a greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
This is a rich cake.
Should not be iced.
Enjoy!

title: walla walla onion pie
directions: Saute onions in oil and butter over low heat until golden yellow.
Beat together the eggs, half and half, flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add onions and half of grated cheese.
Pour into crust; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Garnish with parsley. This makes a great side dish for chicken, beef or pork.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well-greased skillet.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Put the undrained cans of pineapple into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in the sugar and jello until dissolved.
Let cool, then add the buttermilk and fold in the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; add chili powder, garlic salt, cumin, pepper and salt.
Add pinto beans.
In small saucepan, combine the puree, water and enchilada seasoning. Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: *Thin down a little more than when you make icing.

title: apple pie
directions: Fill the pastry shell with apples.
Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg or cinnamon and orange juice.
Pour this mixture over the apples.
Cover apples with 1/2-inch strips of pie pastry. Flute edges and add 1/2 cup melted margarine over pastry. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until the apples are tender.

title: creamy butter cake
directions: Mix cake following box directions and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and lightly flour cake pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix eggs, flour and milk together.
Add enough water to brown sugar to melt it and add butter.
Heat until well blended and let cool, then add to first mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: delicious haddock
directions: Cook fish in small
amount
of water until fork-tender. Drain any remaining liquid.
For
casserole,
flake
fish into large chunks or leave whole if you prefer.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
In
another
pan,
melt
tablespoons butter;
then stir in flour.
When smooth, add milk gradually, stirring until thick.
Continue
stirring and add cheese until melted and well blended.
Season
with
salt
and
pepper; add sherry and mushrooms.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fold egg with cottage cheese and 1/4 bag of Mozzarella cheese. Set aside.

title: delicious salmon loaf
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blender pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients in blender, food processor or mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute with blender or 2 minutes with mixer.
Place in bowl and microwave until thoroughly heated.
Stir frequently.
Pour into glass pie plate.
Microwave on Medium for 15 to 20 minutes.
May need to shield outer edges with foil after 5 to 6 minutes, then continue to cook.
Pie will be done when edges are set and center is still slightly soft.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip on cooled pie.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and cook 1 hour at 350° until hash browns are cooked.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove leaves from head of cabbage.
Place in large pot and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine meat, rice, eggs and salt.
Place a tablespoon of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Fold in sides to cover meat and roll.
Place rolls in large saucepan with open side down.
Combine onions, celery, sugar and tomato soup.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown the meat lightly.
Add the celery and onions in the liquid from browning the meat.
When this is brown add to the meat with 2 cups of water.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add salt to taste. To this mixture add the Chinese vegetables, Chinese bean sprouts, Chinese sauce and cornstarch.
Boil until tender.
When serving, pour the chop suey over boiled rice, if you wish.
Add a little butter, if you wish.
Good.

title: mexican jalapeno corn bread
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch cast iron skillet or cake pan with butter; place in oven while preheating to 350°.
Mix the cornmeal, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Add eggs, sour cream, oil and creamed corn; mix well.
Pour half batter into the hot skillet or cake pan; sprinkle with jalapeno peppers and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over the peppers and cheese.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 wedges.

title: crowd size waikiki meatballs
directions: Stir cracker crumbs, eggs, milk and meat together.
Make into meatballs the size of large golf balls.
Place them on two broiler pans and bake at 350 degrees in oven for 1 hour.
Turn meatballs after 30 minutes.

title: company pickle chunks
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand until next morning.
Drain and do this for the next 3 mornings.
On the 5th day, drain and slice in 1/2 inch pieces.
Combine sugar, salt, spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On the 3rd day, bring to a boil and seal in hot jars.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, soda water and sherbet.
Add these ingredients just before serving.
Serves 40 people.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Note:
May substitute 8 ounces pain low-fat yogurt for the cream and sour cream and eliminate oil and butter.

title: red, white and blue dessert
directions: Whip the cream. In a large bowl, combine milk, water, almond extract and dry pudding mix. Fold whipping cream into pudding mixture and chill for 5 minutes. Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices and arrange on the bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Pour 1/2 of cream mixture over cake, then 1 can of pie filling*. Repeat cake, cream and filling. Tastes best if made the night before.

title: cool whip torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with fingers and press into 9 x 12 pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Beat the next 3 ingredients until fluffy and spread over cooled crust. Beat pudding mix and milk slowly for about 2 minutes and spread over cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip. Makes 4 layers.

title: mini reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon dressing on each slice of bread.
Place 1 tablespoon kraut on top with 1/2 slice corned beef and 1/2 slice Swiss cheese.
Place on baking sheet and broil only to melt cheese.
Makes 24 hors d'oeuvres.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cook broccoli until almost tender; drain.
Blend mayonnaise and lemon juice with soup. Arrange cooked broccoli in baking dish.
Top with chicken slices and pour sauce evenly over all.
Sprinkle with a mixture of bread crumbs and butter.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven 1/2 hour or until topping is lightly browned.
If desired, add 1/4 teaspoon curry powder to sauce mixture; blend well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas and pecans; mash bananas and add to mixture; stir. Add pecans and mix. Pour into loaf pans and bake for 30 to 50 minutes (depending on the size of loaf pans used) at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: In large skillet, cook beef, onions, pepper and garlic in hot oil.
Heat until beef is browned and onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until rice is done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place raw chicken in baking pan. Cover with rice, water, soup, salt and pepper. Put tinfoil over pan; punch holes in tinfoil. Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, shortening and sugar; real good.
Beat in eggs. Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake until light touch with finger leaves slight imprint; about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In saucepan, blend soups together.
Slowly heat through, stirring often.
Garnish with sweet red and green pepper strips and sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups. May be doubled.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into large baking dish.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, milk and melted margarine.
Batter will be slightly lumpy and liquid in consistency.
Pour batter over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until crust is golden brown.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar, milk, egg and oil.
Mix the dry ingredients, stir and add to the first mixture.
Put into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate muffins
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo over low heat; stir in pecans. Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix by hand only until well blended.
Add chocolate and nuts.
Pour into muffin cups. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma ryan's delmonico potatoes
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes to 1/4 inch thick and lay one layer on the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle chopped onion over the potatoes and add a few pats of butter.
Place a layer of cheese over everything and sprinkle with a little flour.
Continue layering up until all of the potatoes have been used and cheese is on top.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Bring water, sugar and cinnamon to a boil, stirring frequently.
Pour nuts out on waxed paper.
After mixture thins a little and boils, pour over nuts.
Let stand to harden.

title: seafood medley(serves 4)
directions: Stir-fry onion, pepper and garlic until tender. Add tomatoes and Port wine. After onions are caramelized, add fish and crabmeat. Add seasoning. Serve over spaghetti or rice (which may be cooked in chicken bouillon flavored water).

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute butter, onion, celery and garlic.
Add chicken broth and rice.
Bring mixture to boil.
Stir once with a fork.
Add shredded carrot or chopped spinach.
Cover, turn to low heat and cook until all liquid is absorbed.

title: wrapped hot dogs
directions: Cut slit in hot dog.
Cut a slice of cheese in half, stuff in hot dog.
Wrap slice of bacon around hot dog.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake on cookie sheet in oven about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chick trick
directions: Boil and debone chicken; tear into small pieces and line bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Heat just to boiling and pour over chicken.
Crumble all crackers over mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizzaburgers(16 sandwiches)
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and pepper together; drain.
Cook all ingredients together, adding cheese last so it stays in chunks. Put on buns, wrap in aluminum foil and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: heavenly out island sandwich
directions: Spread mayonnaise on bread slices; then place layers of first 5 ingredients on one slice of bread.
Put cheese on top of this. Broil until cheese melts.
Put top slice of bread on.
Cut in half and serve!

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fill lined pan with apples.
In a small bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon juice.
Sprinkle mixture over the apples and dot with butter, cut into small pieces.

title: egg salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise and mustard. Gently fold in eggs, cheese and onions just until mixed.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix crab, cream cheese and butter.
Heat in microwave for approximately 2 minutes or until butter and cream cheese melt. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls.
Pinch perforations and edges of rolls together to seal well.
In a small bowl, beat together sugar, vanilla, cream cheese, egg yolk and lemon juice. Spread mixture over rolls.
Cover with other package of rolls.
Beat egg white slightly and brush over rolls.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: arietta stowell's baked beans(modified for no cholesterol)
directions: Sort beans (for hard ones, stones, etc.) as usual.
Fill a large kettle at least 1/2 full of water.
Add beans; bring to a quick boil.
Turn off the heat; let them sit in liquid 1 to 1 1/2 hours (they can sit overnight in a cool place, if desired).
Drain off and reserve liquid.
Leave just enough to cover the beans. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in covered casserole dish.
Bake for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.
Watch carefully to be sure beans don't boil over (lid can be "tipped" to prevent making a mess in your oven).
Bake until beans are tender (easy to mash), adding reserved liquid as needed to keep beans covered.

title: sweet applets
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together; set aside. Mix sugar and shortening, creaming well.
Blend in the egg.
Mix well.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in shredded pared apples.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full in each muffin section.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take out of pans when done baking.
Dip in the melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add strawberries last.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve cold.

title: manhattan meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and seasoning. Mix lightly. Shape into medium meatballs. Brown in margarine.
Place in casserole dish. Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: triple layer chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and lightly flour baking pans. In a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. In a second bowl, mix sour cream, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat into flour mixture about 2 minutes by hand. Spread evenly in baking pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center is clean when removed. Let cool in pans on a wire rack 10 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Cut all meat and cheese into small chunks.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add Italian dressing to taste (should not be a lot of dressing).
Take fresh bread dough or frozen bread dough (cut frozen in half) and roll out with rolling pin.

title: mac 'n cheese with tomatoes
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese by package directions.
Halve cherry tomatoes.
Toss with macaroni; serve.

title: pizza boats
directions: Slice loaf in half lengthwise and scoop out centers, saving bread for croutons or dressing.
Prepare sauce and stir in ground beef.
Sprinkle grated cheese in bottom of each boat; spoon in sauce and meat mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes on top rack of 400° oven.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top; turn off heat and return to oven for a few minutes until cheese is melted. Let stand a few minutes.

title: tuna dish
directions: Cool rice; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight bowl for 24 hours before serving.
Can be served with crackers or chips on lettuce.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Store in airtight container until ready for use.
Mix to taste with 1 cup hot water (milk is not necessary to use as it is already in the mix).

title: frozen mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, then drain.
Add Velveeta cheese until melted, then add crushed potato chips.
If thick, add a little milk.
Place in casserole.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Blend together milk, salt, pepper, egg, mayo and vinegar. Pour over remaining ingredients except peas.
Add peas just before serving.
Make several hours before eating or day ahead.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Mix with first 4 ingredients in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer sauce, then noodles, then cheese (usually 3 layers).
Sprinkle top layer with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until noodles are done.

title: seasoned toasted pecans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Stir well and mix with pecans.
Spread out in a large flat pan and toast in 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Stir during the toasting so nuts will become evenly seasoned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: low cholesterol pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Put all ingredients into a mixing bowl; beat for 10 minutes on medium speed.
Turn batter into Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for meats
directions: Choose at least a 2 pound standing rib.
Allow 3/4 to 1 pound per person.
Season with seasoned salt, onion salt and garlic powder.

title: sugar'd t cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a wooden spoon.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a round baking pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana pecan torte
directions: In a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in bananas and vanilla. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in pecans and pour mixture in three greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: glaze for baked ham
directions: Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in small saucepan.
Stir in crushed pineapple, lemon juice and mustard.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Combine all together and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it is set.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw and drain
broccoli.
Chop onion.
Melt butter and mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Add muffin mix last.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into container; let jell in refrigerator.
When firm, spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Return to refrigerator.

title: rosie's apple walnut pound cake
directions: Beat eggs well, add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add apples and walnuts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Layer broccoli and cheese, leaving last layer on top to be cheese.
Melt butter and crush crackers (in Ziploc baggie with a rolling pin).
Mix butter and crushed crackers.
Top casserole and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chow mein noodle no bake cookies
directions: Melt together chips.
Turn off stove.
Add noodles, peanuts and marshmallows.
Take by teaspoonful and push on wax paper. Refrigerate and keep cookies in refrigerator at all times.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add juice from strawberries to cake batter.
Separate egg whites.
Beat until stiff and fluffy.
Then fold into cake batter.
Mix well.
Heat oven to 350° or 375°. Bake 1 hour.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Mix above ingredients together and press in 9 x 13 pan. Bake 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Place all ingredients in blender until good consistency. Enjoy with chips.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix
sugar, water, cinnamon and cornstarch and bring to boil until butter melts.
Pour over apples and put top crust. Bake at 325° until done.

title: nanci's melt-in-your-mouth venison
directions: Trim and bone steaks.
Cut into 2 to 4-inch squares.
Pound flat with mallet.
Place dressing in bowl.
Cover completely with seasoning salt.
Add 4 shakes of Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Stir well.
Cover baking sheet with foil.
Dip each piece of meat into sauce to cover completely and place on foil.
Pour leftover sauce onto meat.
Broil 3 minutes. Turn and broil another 3 minutes.
(Can be grilled.)

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix together all ingredients and make into small balls.
Press down with floured fork.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over butter.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: chocolate fudge (no bake) cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1-1 1/2 minutes after a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and salt.
Add boiling water.
Blend and cool.
Add to beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Pour into egg mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Refrigerate about 6 hours or overnight.
When ready, take out and knead what you need.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Let rise for about 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sauerkraut pie (one dish meal)(year 1917)
directions: Cook pork until real tender.
Put a layer of sauerkraut and then meat until dish is filled.
Then grate potatoes over top. Then add eggs, salt and pepper.
Bake one hour or until potatoes are done.

title: shortcake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients, then cut in 1/3 cup of shortening.
Add 2 eggs and about 3/4 cup milk.
Just stir eggs and milk in flour and shortening mixture until blended.
Bake in muffin cups.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon poppy seed cake(low-fat and low sugar)
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in large bowl.
Add oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed. Pour batter in Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and drizzle with Lemon Glaze:

title: sweet kugel
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°. In the same pot the noodles were cooked in, mix noodles, cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla; add sour cream, raisins and apples.
Pour the mixture into a greased pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake for 1 hour until done.

title: moist-n-creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake with a large fork. Combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute.
Spoon mixture over cake, allowing liquid to soak into holes in cake.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup of coconut into whipped topping and spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls in half.
Grate ham and cheese in a food processor.
Heat remaining ingredients and then mix in with ham and cheese.
Spread mixture on rolls; place tops on and heat until thoroughly hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shell.	Bake one hour or until set.

title: dave's meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Drain off liquid, if any, after 1/2 hour.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream, then mix with fruits.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and gradually add milk until mixture thickens.
Stir
in cheese and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in onion
and	spinach.
Stir	until smooth and slightly cool. Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into mixture.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350°
until firm on top and soft inside, about 35 minutes.

title: no fail gingerbread cookies
directions: Combine molasses, butter and brown sugar in large pot; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup flour; let cool.
Dissolve the baking soda in the vinegar.
Beat egg.
Add spices to egg. Add egg mixture to soda and vinegar mixture.
Combine with molasses mixture.
Add flour until it is a good consistency for rolling (about 4 to 5 cups).
Rolls out extremely well.
Never sticks.
Good for cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.
These cookies stay nice and soft if stored in an airtight can.
Dough refrigerates and freezes well.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: dill bread
directions: Heat onion, water, cottage cheese and butter to 120°.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar, dill, baking soda, salt, wheat germ, egg and warmed mixture.
Stir well.
Add 1 3/4 cup flour and knead for 3 minutes.
If dough is sticky, add more flour.
Put dough into greased bowl.
Grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Punch down and shape into loaf. Put into greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Brush with melted butter.
Best served warm.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Mix each box of Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Set aside (cool to room temperature).

title: meat loaf casserole
directions: Combine and mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Put in a roaster. Then place some chopped potatoes, carrots and peas all around it. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and raisin salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over first 5.

title: appetizer
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, line 1 package roll. Layer each ingredient as given.

title: winter salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, vegetable oil, salt and pepper in saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Turn sauerkraut into strainer, rinse under running water and drain well.
Place in medium size bowl.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over sauerkraut.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic salt.
Cover and chill 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: praline cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Begin and end with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: macaroni chili
directions: In Dutch oven or heavy large pan, brown meat in oil, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, onions, garlic, salt and remaining seasonings.
Simmer, covered, one hour or more.
Stir in kidney beans and pickles.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf.
Add cooked macaroni.
Makes 10 servings.
Very good and filling meal.

title: bavarian sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut and wash in sieve or colander several times to remove brine. Chop onion and bacon into small pieces; saute until onion is translucent. Cook in a skillet with a lid. Drain off bacon grease. Add sauerkraut mixing with onion and bacon. Wash and core apple. Slice crosswise into 1/4 inch slices. Arrange on top of sauerkraut mixture.
Add apple juice and simmer until juice is reduced by 2/3.
Serve as a side dish. Serves 4.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine; mix with flour and pecans. Press in 9 x 12-inch baking dish to form crust. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes or until brown. Cool. Blend until creamy the sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Set aside. Blend chocolate pudding and milk. Begin with cream cheese mixture and layer alternately with chocolate mixture. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until firm.

title: currant scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in currants.
Combine evaporated milk and egg; add all at once, stirring just until moistened.
On well-floured surface, knead dough gently, 5 or 6 times.
Press into an 8-inch circle about one inch thick; place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cut into 8 wedges; do not separate.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk until well blended.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip lite.
Mix until creamy.
Place in a bowl or dish, alternating layers of pudding mixture, bananas and wafers.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine 2 tablespoons oil, egg and buttermilk.
Stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each frank into 5 pieces.
Dip each piece into batter, coating completely.
Use wooden picks to aid in dipping. Pour oil to depth of 3 to 4-inches into a Dutch oven.
Heat to 375°.

title: salsa mold
directions: Empty Jell-O into 2 cups of boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix together.
Pour into mold and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: portofino salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in pecans and turn into a 2-quart serving bowl or 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
When gelatin is set, soften cream cheese and gradually beat in sour cream until mixture is smooth. Spread over gelatin.
Chill and serve.

title: sunflower nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat margarine in baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, in oven until melted.
Rotate pan until butter covers bottom.
Sprinkle granola evenly over butter.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Shape into a ball or any shape you desire.

title: mexican egg rolls
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet; drain well.
Add chilies, cheese and seasonings; stir well.
Place 2 tablespoons of beef mixture on wrapper.
Fold jelly roll fashion; brush edge of wrapper lightly with water.
Press edges together and seal.
Heat vegetable oil to 375° into large saucepan.
Place 2 or 3 egg rolls in pan; fry 30 seconds on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and pepper in butter for 3 minutes. Add beef; brown, breaking up meat as it cooks.
Add seasoned salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Heat mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place wide noodles, then tomato-meat mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut and serve as you would lasagne.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Place margarine in saucepan with 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Combine eggs and buttermilk; add to margarine, then pour into flour mixture.
Mix until blended.
Pour into large cookie sheet with rim.
(Note: batter will be thin.)
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Note:
Need flat bottom ice cream cones.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice apples
(do not peel).
Heat grease and butter in heavy skillet.
Add apples and
sprinkle
with
sugar.
Fry, turning frequently to avoid sticking, until tender.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in 1 1/2 quart casserole. Bake uncovered in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 hours. Serves 6-8.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crush crackers and add baking powder.
In bowl beat eggs well. Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add crackers and nuts.
Bake in a greased pan lined with waxed paper at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, pepper, and garlic into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large kettle, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour into hot pint jars, and process for 20 minutes in boiling water.

title: steak tips over noodles
directions: Dredge meat in flour and put in baking pan (9 X 13).
Cover with onions, crumble bouillon cubes over meat and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and cook at 375 degrees for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello, then add pineapple to mixture. Mix well.
Add whipped topping; mix well.
Chill overnight or 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all in nonstick baking dish.
Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours.
Keep checking until cooked done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt.
Beat egg well; add to milk. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into Pyrex.
Bake in a pan of water at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, water and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until dough holds together.
(If dough is dry, stir in 1 to 2 teaspoons of water.)
Heat oven to 350°.
For each cookie, group 3 to 5 pecan halves split if necessary on ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls around caramel pieces.
Press firmly onto center of each group of nuts.
Bake until set but not brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and dip tops of cookies into Chocolate Glaze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs, water, oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Blend.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or 3 small 10 ounce loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: potato pizza supreme
directions: Brown hamburger and onion slightly.
Drain. Sprinkle with salt and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine oregano and tomato sauce. Spread over meat.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil for 3 minutes, drain and spread over meat mixture.
Spread cheese soup over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and add pepperoni slices and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake another 15 minutes without foil.

title: italian salad or garnish for salad
directions: *Or use packet and add red wine vinegar.

title: bacon curry coleslaw
directions: Combine, cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: white chili
directions: Saute chicken and onion about 5 minutes.
Add seasonings, green chiles and chicken broth.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add white beans.
Serve with chopped green onion and sour cream.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix juices; add sugar and water.
